0 fallback block).\n- Growth stage tables, emoji and ascii, keyed by a stage enum/string:\n  - emoji: start `🌱`, progress `🌿`, near-win `🌷`, win `🌻`, loss `🥀`\n  - ascii: a distinct printable token per stage, all pure ASCII (e.g.\n    `seedling` / `growing` / `budding` / `bloom!` / `wilted`, or `*`).\n- `TITLE = \"Word Garden\"` with emoji `🌱` prefix in emoji mode, plain in ascii.\n\nHelpers:\n- `_stage(state) -> str`: derive stage from progress. Logic:\n  - if `state.won` (or is_won): `win`\n  - elif `state.game_over` and not won: `loss`\n  - else compute fraction of distinct secret letters revealed:\n    revealed/total. `start` when 0 (no correct letters yet), `near-win`\n    when only 1 letter (or <=1) remains hidden, `progress` otherwise.\n  - Edge: a 1-distinct-letter word — guard so \"start\" vs \"near-win\" still\n    sane; near-win should mean \"almost there\", so base it on letters\n    remaining, not raw count.\n- `_water_line(state, ascii_mode)`: label + count + symbols. MUST be\n  `Water: <remaining>/<max> ` then `remaining` filled symbols (and per\n  SPEC §18 example the count text is always present). Decide whether to\n  also show empty slots — show filled = remaining, and the `n/max` count\n  carries the rest. Never symbols alone.\n- `_weed_line`: `Weeds: <count> ` + count weed symbols.\n- `_guessed_line`: sorted, space-separated guessed letters.\n\nPublic:\n- `render(state, ascii_mode=False) -> str` — assembles, in SPEC §9 order:\n  title, plant/garden status (stage glyph + maybe word like \"Garden:\"),\n  `Word: ` + `display_word(state)`, `Guessed: ` + sorted letters,\n  water line, weeds line, blank line, previous `status_message`.\n  Returns a single string (no trailing prompt — main.py prints the prompt).\n- `win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)` — SPEC §6.6: stage glyph `🌻` /\n  ascii, \"Bloom!\", \"You guessed the word: WORD\", \"The garden is thriving.\"\n- `loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)` — SPEC §6.7: `🥀`/ascii, \"The\n  garden ran out of water.\", \"The word was: WORD\", \"Try again...\".\n  MUST reveal `state.secret_word`.\n\nCritical: in `ascii_mode=True`, EVERY character of EVERY output (render,\nwin, loss, all stages, water/weed symbols) must be ASCII (`s.isascii()`).\nThis includes end screens — a common miss.\n\n## main.py — the ONLY I/O module\n\n- `main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int`:\n  - argparse: `--difficulty {easy,normal,hard}` default `normal`,\n    `--ascii` store_true. NEVER wrap parse_args in try/except SystemExit\n    (so --help exits 0, usage error exits 2). `argv` passed to\n    `parse_args(argv)`.\n  - `state = new_game(args.difficulty)` (production RNG, rng=None).\n  - Loop:\n    - `output_fn(ui.render(state, ascii))`\n    - read with `input_fn(\"Guess a letter: \")` inside try for EOFError /\n      KeyboardInterrupt -> friendly goodbye via output_fn, return 0.\n    - `letter, err = validate_guess(raw)`; if err: `output_fn(err)`,\n      continue WITHOUT touching state (no water consumed).\n    - `state = apply_guess(state, letter)` (reassign!).\n    - if `state.game_over`: break.\n  - After loop: `output_fn(win_screen if state.won else loss_screen)`,\n    return 0.\n- `__main__.py`: `from .main import main; raise SystemExit(main())` —\n  propagate the return code.\n\n## tests/test_ui.py\n\nBuild fixtures by constructing `GameState(...)` directly with pinned\nvalues (no `new_game()` then overwrite — RNG leak). Import message/glyph\nconstants, don't retype literals.\n\n- render emoji: asserts labels AND counts present (\"Water:\", \"4/6\",\n  contains 💧) — positive assertion.\n- render ascii: assert `out.isascii()` is True (positive, whole-string) AND\n  labels/counts present.\n- growth stages: construct states at start (no guesses), mid (some), near-\n  win (one letter left), win state, loss state; assert correct stage glyph\n  appears in render/screens.\n- win_screen and loss_screen: assert word revealed, correct headline.\n- e2e win: inject `input_fn` returning scripted letters that spell a known\n  word (force the word by injecting rng via... but main calls new_game with\n  no rng — so monkeypatch `words._random`/select, OR seed; per tips, force\n  a known scenario). Assert win screen text appeared in captured output.\n- e2e loss: scripted wrong letters until water gone; assert loss screen +\n  word appeared. Assert exact terminal message, not just exit code.\n\nNote: main() uses production `new_game` (rng=None) — to make e2e\ndeterministic, the test must monkeypatch the randomness source (e.g.\n`words.WORDS` or `random.choice`) to pin the secret word, then drive\ninput to a known win/loss. Asserting an OR of outcomes proves nothing.\n\n## Risks / things I will check in candidates\n\n1. ASCII purity in END SCREENS, not just render. Easy to forget the win\n   `🌻` / loss `🥀` glyph in ascii mode.\n2. Water line must carry BOTH text count and symbol per §18 — not symbols\n   only; and not count only.\n3. Invalid input must `continue` before apply_guess so no water consumed —\n   verify the control flow, not just the message.\n4. Reassigning `state = apply_guess(...)` — engine returns new object.\n5. argparse: no SystemExit swallowing; usage error exit 2, --help exit 0.\n6. EOF AND KeyboardInterrupt both caught; return 0; no traceback.\n7. Growth stage thresholds: near-win must actually trigger before win;\n   off-by-one on \"letters remaining\" is the likely bug.\n8. e2e tests must pin randomness, not assert an OR of acceptable outputs.\n9. No print/input in ui.py; main.py the only stdio module; engine bytes\n   untouched.\n10. README present with §19 intro, run instructions, rules, sample screen.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_019dGgzT6J3dLyK2NE4W6skQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Blind sketch committed. Now reading the candidate diffs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5243,"cache_read_input_tokens":35207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5243},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"b2231fe6-4003-44d7-a9ed-6ffeb7b5d539","request_id":"req_011Cbxgr1Y74WvaCKy3HiXT6"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_019dGgzT6J3dLyK2NE4W6skQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MzJxeJ5yHRJhjS6C8M15EK","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"ls -la .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/ && wc -l .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/*.diff","description":"List candidate diffs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5243,"cache_read_input_tokens":35207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5243},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"854be47f-5974-43a0-a754-3d770e7894dc","request_id":"req_011Cbxgr1Y74WvaCKy3HiXT6"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MzJxeJ5yHRJhjS6C8M15EK","type":"tool_result","content":"total 88\ndrwxr-xr-x@  5 rob  staff    160 12 Jun 15:51 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 10 rob  staff    320 12 Jun 15:52 ..\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff  23959 12 Jun 15:51 A.diff\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff  19922 12 Jun 15:51 B.diff\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff      0 12 Jun 15:51 C.diff\n     656 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/A.diff\n     647 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/B.diff\n       0 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/C.diff\n    1303 total","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"621f359b-f56a-4fbf-be56-03016c3ea46d","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:52:50.000Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"total 88\ndrwxr-xr-x@  5 rob  staff    160 12 Jun 15:51 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 10 rob  staff    320 12 Jun 15:52 ..\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff  23959 12 Jun 15:51 A.diff\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff  19922 12 Jun 15:51 B.diff\n-rw-r--r--@  1 rob  staff      0 12 Jun 15:51 C.diff\n     656 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/A.diff\n     647 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/B.diff\n       0 .farnsworth/task-002/candidates/C.diff\n    1303 total","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01DdJcxVoQv2e2XaPuwypQCE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":40450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"29b53d43-f9a5-42c3-af6e-1546bef79c89","request_id":"req_011CbxgrJHAxfCzQN6YdLYaW"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01DdJcxVoQv2e2XaPuwypQCE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Candidate C is an empty diff (0 bytes) — a non-submission. Let me read A and B."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":40450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"57101d40-35bf-44e2-8502-e2d9062a5aed","request_id":"req_011CbxgrJHAxfCzQN6YdLYaW"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01DdJcxVoQv2e2XaPuwypQCE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0181EMWWjsFEQoETsaRW8uJv","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates/A.diff"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":40450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"5316cd84-645a-4e69-8d65-220a72f315a9","request_id":"req_011CbxgrJHAxfCzQN6YdLYaW"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0181EMWWjsFEQoETsaRW8uJv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tdiff --git a/README.md b/README.md\n2\tnew file mode 100644\n3\tindex 0000000..604b36f\n4\t--- /dev/null\n5\t+++ b/README.md\n6\t@@ -0,0 +1,98 @@\n7\t+# Word Garden 🌱\n8\t+\n9\t+> Word Garden is a small TUI game designed as a more cheerful alternative to\n10\t+> Hangman. It is intended as a slightly more adventurous \"Hello World\" project\n11\t+> for testing AI-assisted software development. The game includes input\n12\t+> validation, state management, a simple loop, win/loss conditions, and a\n13\t+> friendly terminal interface.\n14\t+\n15\t+Guess the hidden word before the garden runs out of water. Each correct guess\n16\t+helps the garden grow; each wrong guess costs a drop of water and lets a weed\n17\t+appear. Reveal the whole word to make the garden bloom — it's like Hangman,\n18\t+but with plants instead of gallows.\n19\t+\n20\t+## Requirements\n21\t+\n22\t+- Python 3.11 or newer (standard library only — nothing to install).\n23\t+\n24\t+## How to run\n25\t+\n26\t+```bash\n27\t+python3 -m word_garden\n28\t+```\n29\t+\n30\t+Options:\n31\t+\n32\t+```bash\n33\t+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty easy    # easy | normal | hard (default: normal)\n34\t+python3 -m word_garden --ascii              # pure-ASCII display for terminals without emoji\n35\t+```\n36\t+\n37\t+`--difficulty` changes both the starting water and the pool of words:\n38\t+\n39\t+| Difficulty | Water | Word length |\n40\t+|---|---:|---:|\n41\t+| easy   | 8 | 4–6 letters |\n42\t+| normal | 6 | 5–8 letters |\n43\t+| hard   | 4 | 7+ letters  |\n44\t+\n45\t+## How to play\n46\t+\n47\t+1. The game picks a secret word and shows one blank per letter.\n48\t+2. Type a single letter and press Enter at the `Guess a letter:` prompt.\n49\t+3. A correct guess reveals every matching position in the word.\n50\t+4. A wrong guess costs one unit of water and adds one weed.\n51\t+5. Repeated or invalid input (empty, multiple characters, digits, symbols)\n52\t+   is rejected with a friendly message and does **not** cost a turn.\n53\t+6. You win when the whole word is revealed; you lose if water reaches zero\n54\t+   first. Press Ctrl-D or Ctrl-C at any time to leave the garden cleanly.\n55\t+\n56\t+## Sample screen\n57\t+\n58\t+```text\n59\t+🌱 Word Garden\n60\t+\n61\t+Garden:  🌿  The garden is growing.\n62\t+Word:    G _ R _ E _\n63\t+Guessed: A E G R\n64\t+Water:   4/6 💧💧💧💧\n65\t+Weeds:   2 🌿🌿\n66\t+\n67\t+Good guess! The garden grows.\n68\t+\n69\t+Guess a letter:\n70\t+```\n71\t+\n72\t+The same turn in `--ascii` mode:\n73\t+\n74\t+```text\n75\t+Word Garden\n76\t+\n77\t+Garden:  **  The garden is growing.\n78\t+Word:    G _ R _ E _\n79\t+Guessed: A E G R\n80\t+Water:   4/6 [****  ]\n81\t+Weeds:   2 [--]\n82\t+\n83\t+Good guess! The garden grows.\n84\t+\n85\t+Guess a letter:\n86\t+```\n87\t+\n88\t+## Project layout\n89\t+\n90\t+```text\n91\t+word_garden/\n92\t+  __main__.py   # python3 -m word_garden entry point\n93\t+  main.py       # argument parsing and the game loop (the only I/O module)\n94\t+  game.py       # game state, guesses, win/loss logic\n95\t+  words.py      # word list and difficulty filtering\n96\t+  ui.py         # pure rendering (returns strings; no printing)\n97\t+tests/          # unittest suite (engine + UI)\n98\t+```\n99\t+\n100\t+## Running the tests\n101\t+\n102\t+```bash\n103\t+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests\n104\t+```\n105\tdiff --git a/tests/test_ui.py b/tests/test_ui.py\n106\tnew file mode 100644\n107\tindex 0000000..774d9dd\n108\t--- /dev/null\n109\t+++ b/tests/test_ui.py\n110\t@@ -0,0 +1,290 @@\n111\t+import unittest\n112\t+from unittest import mock\n113\t+\n114\t+from word_garden.game import GameState\n115\t+from word_garden import main as main_module\n116\t+from word_garden.main import GOODBYE, PROMPT, main\n117\t+from word_garden.ui import (\n118\t+    GROWTH_STAGES,\n119\t+    LOSS_BODY,\n120\t+    LOSS_HEADER,\n121\t+    LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE,\n122\t+    STAGE_LOSS,\n123\t+    STAGE_NEAR_WIN,\n124\t+    STAGE_PROGRESS,\n125\t+    STAGE_START,\n126\t+    STAGE_WIN,\n127\t+    WATER_EMOJI,\n128\t+    WEED_EMOJI,\n129\t+    WIN_BODY,\n130\t+    WIN_HEADER,\n131\t+    WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE,\n132\t+    growth_stage,\n133\t+    loss_screen,\n134\t+    render,\n135\t+    win_screen,\n136\t+)\n137\t+\n138\t+\n139\t+def _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n140\t+    \"\"\"Build a GameState directly with pinned values (no randomness).\"\"\"\n141\t+    defaults = dict(\n142\t+        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n143\t+        guessed_letters=set(),\n144\t+        remaining_water=6,\n145\t+        weed_count=0,\n146\t+        max_water=6,\n147\t+    )\n148\t+    defaults.update(kwargs)\n149\t+    return GameState(**defaults)\n150\t+\n151\t+\n152\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n153\t+# render — emoji mode\n154\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n155\t+\n156\t+class TestRenderEmoji(unittest.TestCase):\n157\t+    def test_contains_title_and_word_and_guesses(self):\n158\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"R\"})\n159\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n160\t+        self.assertIn(\"Word Garden\", out)\n161\t+        self.assertIn(\"G _ R _ _ _\", out)\n162\t+        # Guessed letters sorted and space-separated.\n163\t+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", out)\n164\t+        self.assertIn(\"G R\", out)\n165\t+\n166\t+    def test_water_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n167\t+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6)\n168\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n169\t+        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", out)\n170\t+        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", out)\n171\t+        self.assertIn(WATER_EMOJI * 4, out)\n172\t+\n173\t+    def test_weeds_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n174\t+        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n175\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n176\t+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", out)\n177\t+        self.assertIn(\"2\", out)\n178\t+        self.assertIn(WEED_EMOJI * 2, out)\n179\t+\n180\t+    def test_status_message_shown_when_present(self):\n181\t+        state = _make_state(status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\")\n182\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n183\t+        self.assertIn(\"No match. A weed appears.\", out)\n184\t+\n185\t+    def test_empty_status_message_not_rendered_as_blank_feedback(self):\n186\t+        # A fresh game has no feedback line; the last line is the weeds row.\n187\t+        state = _make_state()\n188\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n189\t+        self.assertTrue(out.rstrip().endswith(render(state).splitlines()[-1]))\n190\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"None\", out)\n191\t+\n192\t+\n193\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n194\t+# render — ASCII mode (must be pure ASCII)\n195\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n196\t+\n197\t+class TestRenderAscii(unittest.TestCase):\n198\t+    def test_output_is_pure_ascii(self):\n199\t+        state = _make_state(\n200\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n201\t+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"Z\"},\n202\t+            remaining_water=5,\n203\t+            weed_count=1,\n204\t+            status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\",\n205\t+        )\n206\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n207\t+        self.assertTrue(out.isascii(), f\"non-ASCII characters found: {out!r}\")\n208\t+\n209\t+    def test_ascii_has_labels_count_and_no_emoji(self):\n210\t+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6, weed_count=2)\n211\t+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n212\t+        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", out)\n213\t+        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", out)\n214\t+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", out)\n215\t+        self.assertNotIn(WATER_EMOJI, out)\n216\t+        self.assertNotIn(WEED_EMOJI, out)\n217\t+\n218\t+    def test_ascii_win_loss_screens_pure_ascii(self):\n219\t+        won = _make_state(\n220\t+            guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"), game_over=True, won=True\n221\t+        )\n222\t+        lost = _make_state(remaining_water=0, weed_count=6, game_over=True)\n223\t+        self.assertTrue(win_screen(won, ascii_mode=True).isascii())\n224\t+        self.assertTrue(loss_screen(lost, ascii_mode=True).isascii())\n225\t+\n226\t+\n227\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n228\t+# growth stages (SPEC §10): start / progress / near-win / win / loss\n229\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n230\t+\n231\t+class TestGrowthStages(unittest.TestCase):\n232\t+    def test_start_when_nothing_revealed(self):\n233\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n234\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_START)\n235\t+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_START][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n236\t+\n237\t+    def test_progress_when_some_revealed(self):\n238\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\"})\n239\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_PROGRESS)\n240\t+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_PROGRESS][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n241\t+\n242\t+    def test_near_win_when_one_letter_left(self):\n243\t+        # GARDEN with all but N revealed → exactly one secret letter remains.\n244\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"})\n245\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_NEAR_WIN)\n246\t+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_NEAR_WIN][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n247\t+\n248\t+    def test_win_stage_when_won(self):\n249\t+        state = _make_state(guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"), game_over=True, won=True)\n250\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_WIN)\n251\t+\n252\t+    def test_loss_stage_when_lost(self):\n253\t+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=0, weed_count=6, game_over=True, won=False)\n254\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_LOSS)\n255\t+\n256\t+    def test_wrong_guesses_alone_do_not_count_as_progress(self):\n257\t+        # Only wrong letters guessed → no secret letter revealed → still start.\n258\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"Z\", \"Q\"})\n259\t+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_START)\n260\t+\n261\t+\n262\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n263\t+# win / loss screens (SPEC §6.6 / §6.7)\n264\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n265\t+\n266\t+class TestEndScreens(unittest.TestCase):\n267\t+    def test_win_screen_names_word_and_message(self):\n268\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"),\n269\t+                            game_over=True, won=True)\n270\t+        out = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n271\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, out)\n272\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), out)\n273\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, out)\n274\t+        self.assertIn(\"GARDEN\", out)\n275\t+\n276\t+    def test_loss_screen_reveals_secret_word(self):\n277\t+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"PLANET\", remaining_water=0, weed_count=4,\n278\t+                            game_over=True, won=False)\n279\t+        out = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n280\t+        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER, out)\n281\t+        self.assertIn(LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"PLANET\"), out)\n282\t+        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, out)\n283\t+        self.assertIn(\"PLANET\", out)\n284\t+\n285\t+\n286\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n287\t+# end-to-end main() runs with injected I/O\n288\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n289\t+\n290\t+class _Recorder:\n291\t+    \"\"\"Collects output_fn calls; serves scripted input_fn responses.\"\"\"\n292\t+\n293\t+    def __init__(self, inputs):\n294\t+        self._inputs = iter(inputs)\n295\t+        self.outputs: list[str] = []\n296\t+\n297\t+    def input_fn(self, prompt=\"\"):\n298\t+        return next(self._inputs)\n299\t+\n300\t+    def output_fn(self, text=\"\"):\n301\t+        self.outputs.append(str(text))\n302\t+\n303\t+    @property\n304\t+    def text(self) -> str:\n305\t+        return \"\\n\".join(self.outputs)\n306\t+\n307\t+\n308\t+class TestMainEndToEnd(unittest.TestCase):\n309\t+    def test_full_win_shows_win_screen(self):\n310\t+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n311\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n312\t+            code = main([\"--difficulty\", \"normal\"],\n313\t+                        input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n314\t+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n315\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, rec.text)\n316\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), rec.text)\n317\t+\n318\t+    def test_full_loss_shows_loss_screen_with_word(self):\n319\t+        # Six wrong guesses (none in GARDEN) exhaust the normal water of 6.\n320\t+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n321\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n322\t+            code = main([\"--difficulty\", \"normal\"],\n323\t+                        input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n324\t+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n325\t+        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER, rec.text)\n326\t+        self.assertIn(LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), rec.text)\n327\t+\n328\t+    def test_invalid_input_reprompts_without_consuming_water(self):\n329\t+        # Two invalid inputs, then win. Game still won → invalids cost no turn.\n330\t+        rec = _Recorder([\"\", \"7\", \"!\"] + list(\"GARDEN\"))\n331\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n332\t+            code = main([], input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n333\t+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n334\t+        # Validation messages surfaced.\n335\t+        self.assertIn(\"Please enter a single letter.\", rec.text)\n336\t+        self.assertIn(\"That is not a letter.\", rec.text)\n337\t+        # And the game still reached the win screen.\n338\t+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, rec.text)\n339\t+\n340\t+    def test_ascii_mode_run_is_pure_ascii(self):\n341\t+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n342\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n343\t+            main([\"--ascii\"], input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n344\t+        self.assertTrue(rec.text.isascii(), f\"non-ASCII in output: {rec.text!r}\")\n345\t+\n346\t+    def test_difficulty_easy_sets_water_to_eight(self):\n347\t+        # First rendered frame should show the easy starting water of 8/8.\n348\t+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n349\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n350\t+            main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"],\n351\t+                 input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n352\t+        self.assertIn(\"8/8\", rec.outputs[0])\n353\t+\n354\t+    def test_eof_exits_cleanly_with_goodbye(self):\n355\t+        def eof_input(prompt=\"\"):\n356\t+            raise EOFError\n357\t+\n358\t+        outputs = []\n359\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n360\t+            code = main([], input_fn=eof_input, output_fn=lambda t=\"\": outputs.append(str(t)))\n361\t+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n362\t+        self.assertIn(GOODBYE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n363\t+\n364\t+    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exits_cleanly_with_goodbye(self):\n365\t+        def interrupt_input(prompt=\"\"):\n366\t+            raise KeyboardInterrupt\n367\t+\n368\t+        outputs = []\n369\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n370\t+            code = main([], input_fn=interrupt_input,\n371\t+                        output_fn=lambda t=\"\": outputs.append(str(t)))\n372\t+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n373\t+        self.assertIn(GOODBYE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n374\t+\n375\t+    def test_help_exits_zero(self):\n376\t+        with self.assertRaises(SystemExit) as ctx:\n377\t+            main([\"--help\"], input_fn=lambda p=\"\": \"\", output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n378\t+        self.assertEqual(ctx.exception.code, 0)\n379\t+\n380\t+    def test_bad_difficulty_exits_two(self):\n381\t+        with self.assertRaises(SystemExit) as ctx:\n382\t+            main([\"--difficulty\", \"impossible\"],\n383\t+                 input_fn=lambda p=\"\": \"\", output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n384\t+        self.assertEqual(ctx.exception.code, 2)\n385\t+\n386\t+    def test_prompt_text_is_passed_to_input(self):\n387\t+        seen = []\n388\t+\n389\t+        def capture_input(prompt=\"\"):\n390\t+            seen.append(prompt)\n391\t+            return next(letters)\n392\t+\n393\t+        letters = iter(\"GARDEN\")\n394\t+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n395\t+            main([], input_fn=capture_input, output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n396\t+        self.assertEqual(seen[0], PROMPT)\n397\t+\n398\t+\n399\t+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n400\t+    unittest.main()\n401\tdiff --git a/word_garden/__main__.py b/word_garden/__main__.py\n402\tnew file mode 100644\n403\tindex 0000000..cc88885\n404\t--- /dev/null\n405\t+++ b/word_garden/__main__.py\n406\t@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n407\t+\"\"\"Allow ``python3 -m word_garden`` to launch the game.\"\"\"\n408\t+\n409\t+from .main import main\n410\t+\n411\t+raise SystemExit(main())\n412\tdiff --git a/word_garden/main.py b/word_garden/main.py\n413\tnew file mode 100644\n414\tindex 0000000..2b11073\n415\t--- /dev/null\n416\t+++ b/word_garden/main.py\n417\t@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\n418\t+\"\"\"Command-line entry point and game loop for Word Garden.\n419\t+\n420\t+This is the ONLY module that touches stdin/stdout. All terminal interaction\n421\t+goes through the injectable ``input_fn``/``output_fn`` so the loop is testable\n422\t+without a real terminal.\n423\t+\"\"\"\n424\t+\n425\t+import argparse\n426\t+\n427\t+from .game import apply_guess, new_game, validate_guess\n428\t+from .ui import loss_screen, render, win_screen\n429\t+\n430\t+PROMPT = \"Guess a letter: \"\n431\t+GOODBYE = \"Thanks for visiting the garden. Come back soon!\"\n432\t+\n433\t+_DIFFICULTIES = [\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"]\n434\t+\n435\t+\n436\t+def _build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n437\t+    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n438\t+        prog=\"word_garden\",\n439\t+        description=\"Word Garden — a friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n440\t+    )\n441\t+    parser.add_argument(\n442\t+        \"--difficulty\",\n443\t+        choices=_DIFFICULTIES,\n444\t+        default=\"normal\",\n445\t+        help=\"word length and starting water (default: normal).\",\n446\t+    )\n447\t+    parser.add_argument(\n448\t+        \"--ascii\",\n449\t+        action=\"store_true\",\n450\t+        help=\"use the pure-ASCII display instead of emoji.\",\n451\t+    )\n452\t+    return parser\n453\t+\n454\t+\n455\t+def main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int:\n456\t+    \"\"\"Run a full game and return the process exit code (0).\n457\t+\n458\t+    ``input_fn`` and ``output_fn`` default to the builtins but may be injected\n459\t+    for testing. Note: ``parse_args`` is intentionally NOT wrapped in\n460\t+    try/except — ``--help`` must exit 0 and a usage error must exit 2.\n461\t+    \"\"\"\n462\t+    args = _build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n463\t+    ascii_mode = args.ascii\n464\t+    state = new_game(args.difficulty)\n465\t+\n466\t+    try:\n467\t+        while not state.game_over:\n468\t+            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode))\n469\t+            output_fn(\"\")\n470\t+            raw = input_fn(PROMPT)\n471\t+            letter, error = validate_guess(raw)\n472\t+            if letter is None:\n473\t+                # Invalid input: show the message and re-prompt without\n474\t+                # consuming a turn (SPEC §6.2/§14).\n475\t+                output_fn(error)\n476\t+                continue\n477\t+            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n478\t+\n479\t+        screen = (\n480\t+            win_screen(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode)\n481\t+            if state.won\n482\t+            else loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode)\n483\t+        )\n484\t+        output_fn(screen)\n485\t+        return 0\n486\t+    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n487\t+        # Ctrl-D / Ctrl-C: friendly goodbye, clean exit, never a traceback.\n488\t+        output_fn(\"\")\n489\t+        output_fn(GOODBYE)\n490\t+        return 0\n491\tdiff --git a/word_garden/ui.py b/word_garden/ui.py\n492\tnew file mode 100644\n493\tindex 0000000..bb37e31\n494\t--- /dev/null\n495\t+++ b/word_garden/ui.py\n496\t@@ -0,0 +1,160 @@\n497\t+\"\"\"Pure rendering for Word Garden.\n498\t+\n499\t+Every function in this module returns a string. There is deliberately no\n500\t+``print()``/``input()`` here — all I/O lives in :mod:`word_garden.main`.\n501\t+Both an emoji display and a pure-ASCII fallback (SPEC §10, §18) are supported.\n502\t+\"\"\"\n503\t+\n504\t+from .game import GameState, display_word\n505\t+\n506\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n507\t+# Growth-stage visuals (SPEC §10).\n508\t+#\n509\t+# Single source of truth: each stage maps to its emoji glyph, its ASCII\n510\t+# fallback glyph (no non-ASCII characters), and a friendly text label. The\n511\t+# render status line, the win screen, and the loss screen all read from here\n512\t+# so the table is never duplicated.\n513\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n514\t+\n515\t+STAGE_START = \"start\"\n516\t+STAGE_PROGRESS = \"progress\"\n517\t+STAGE_NEAR_WIN = \"near_win\"\n518\t+STAGE_WIN = \"win\"\n519\t+STAGE_LOSS = \"loss\"\n520\t+\n521\t+GROWTH_STAGES: dict[str, dict[str, str]] = {\n522\t+    STAGE_START:    {\"emoji\": \"🌱\", \"ascii\": \"*\",    \"label\": \"A seedling sprouts.\"},\n523\t+    STAGE_PROGRESS: {\"emoji\": \"🌿\", \"ascii\": \"**\",   \"label\": \"The garden is growing.\"},\n524\t+    STAGE_NEAR_WIN: {\"emoji\": \"🌷\", \"ascii\": \"***\",  \"label\": \"Buds are about to bloom.\"},\n525\t+    STAGE_WIN:      {\"emoji\": \"🌻\", \"ascii\": \"\\\\o/\",  \"label\": \"Bloom!\"},\n526\t+    STAGE_LOSS:     {\"emoji\": \"🥀\", \"ascii\": \"x_x\",  \"label\": \"Wilted.\"},\n527\t+}\n528\t+\n529\t+# Resource symbols (SPEC §10).\n530\t+WATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\n531\t+WEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n532\t+WATER_ASCII = \"*\"\n533\t+WEED_ASCII = \"-\"\n534\t+\n535\t+# Layout: label column width shared by every row of the status block.\n536\t+_LABEL_WIDTH = 9\n537\t+\n538\t+# Title (SPEC §5/§9). The title always shows the seedling glyph; the dynamic\n539\t+# growth stage is shown on its own \"Garden:\" line below.\n540\t+TITLE_TEXT = \"Word Garden\"\n541\t+\n542\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n543\t+# End-screen message strings (SPEC §6.6 win / §6.7 loss).\n544\t+#\n545\t+# These are screen-layout strings owned by the UI, distinct from the engine's\n546\t+# one-line ``status_message`` constants. Defined once here; tests import them.\n547\t+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n548\t+\n549\t+WIN_HEADER = \"Bloom!\"\n550\t+WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE = \"You guessed the word: {word}\"\n551\t+WIN_BODY = \"The garden is thriving.\"\n552\t+\n553\t+LOSS_HEADER = \"The garden ran out of water.\"\n554\t+LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE = \"The word was: {word}\"\n555\t+LOSS_BODY = \"Try again and grow a new garden.\"\n556\t+\n557\t+\n558\t+def growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n559\t+    \"\"\"Return the growth-stage key for ``state`` (a key of GROWTH_STAGES).\n560\t+\n561\t+    Driven by progress per SPEC §10: a terminal state is win or loss; before\n562\t+    that it is start (nothing revealed), near-win (one secret letter left),\n563\t+    or progress (something revealed but more than one letter remains).\n564\t+    \"\"\"\n565\t+    if state.game_over and state.won:\n566\t+        return STAGE_WIN\n567\t+    if state.game_over:\n568\t+        return STAGE_LOSS\n569\t+    secret_letters = set(state.secret_word)\n570\t+    revealed = secret_letters & state.guessed_letters\n571\t+    if not revealed:\n572\t+        return STAGE_START\n573\t+    if len(secret_letters - state.guessed_letters) <= 1:\n574\t+        return STAGE_NEAR_WIN\n575\t+    return STAGE_PROGRESS\n576\t+\n577\t+\n578\t+def _glyph(stage: str, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n579\t+    return GROWTH_STAGES[stage][\"ascii\" if ascii_mode else \"emoji\"]\n580\t+\n581\t+\n582\t+def _label(text: str, value: str) -> str:\n583\t+    return f\"{text:<{_LABEL_WIDTH}}{value}\".rstrip()\n584\t+\n585\t+\n586\t+def _water_line(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n587\t+    \"\"\"Water row with text label AND count AND symbols (SPEC §18).\"\"\"\n588\t+    count = f\"{state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water}\"\n589\t+    if ascii_mode:\n590\t+        used = state.max_water - state.remaining_water\n591\t+        symbols = \"[\" + WATER_ASCII * state.remaining_water + \" \" * used + \"]\"\n592\t+    else:\n593\t+        symbols = WATER_EMOJI * state.remaining_water\n594\t+    return _label(\"Water:\", f\"{count} {symbols}\")\n595\t+\n596\t+\n597\t+def _weeds_line(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n598\t+    \"\"\"Weeds row with text label AND count AND symbols (SPEC §18).\"\"\"\n599\t+    count = str(state.weed_count)\n600\t+    if ascii_mode:\n601\t+        symbols = \"[\" + WEED_ASCII * state.weed_count + \"]\"\n602\t+    else:\n603\t+        symbols = WEED_EMOJI * state.weed_count\n604\t+    return _label(\"Weeds:\", f\"{count} {symbols}\")\n605\t+\n606\t+\n607\t+def render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n608\t+    \"\"\"Return the full turn display (SPEC §9), as a string.\n609\t+\n610\t+    Order: title, garden/plant status, masked word, guessed letters, water,\n611\t+    weeds, then the previous turn's ``status_message`` (omitted when empty).\n612\t+    \"\"\"\n613\t+    stage = growth_stage(state)\n614\t+    if ascii_mode:\n615\t+        title = TITLE_TEXT\n616\t+    else:\n617\t+        title = f\"{GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_START]['emoji']} {TITLE_TEXT}\"\n618\t+\n619\t+    garden_value = f\"{_glyph(stage, ascii_mode)}  {GROWTH_STAGES[stage]['label']}\"\n620\t+    guessed = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters))\n621\t+\n622\t+    lines = [\n623\t+        title,\n624\t+        \"\",\n625\t+        _label(\"Garden:\", garden_value),\n626\t+        _label(\"Word:\", display_word(state)),\n627\t+        _label(\"Guessed:\", guessed),\n628\t+        _water_line(state, ascii_mode),\n629\t+        _weeds_line(state, ascii_mode),\n630\t+    ]\n631\t+    if state.status_message:\n632\t+        lines.append(\"\")\n633\t+        lines.append(state.status_message)\n634\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n635\t+\n636\t+\n637\t+def win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n638\t+    \"\"\"Return the winning end screen (SPEC §6.6); names the secret word.\"\"\"\n639\t+    lines = [\n640\t+        f\"{_glyph(STAGE_WIN, ascii_mode)} {WIN_HEADER}\",\n641\t+        \"\",\n642\t+        WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=state.secret_word),\n643\t+        WIN_BODY,\n644\t+    ]\n645\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n646\t+\n647\t+\n648\t+def loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n649\t+    \"\"\"Return the losing end screen (SPEC §6.7); reveals the secret word.\"\"\"\n650\t+    lines = [\n651\t+        f\"{_glyph(STAGE_LOSS, ascii_mode)} {LOSS_HEADER}\",\n652\t+        \"\",\n653\t+        LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=state.secret_word),\n654\t+        LOSS_BODY,\n655\t+    ]\n656\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n657\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"d1eee305-e3bd-4512-b823-e93c62c82f88","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:52:53.691Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates/A.diff","content":"diff --git a/README.md b/README.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..604b36f\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/README.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,98 @@\n+# Word Garden 🌱\n+\n+> Word Garden is a small TUI game designed as a more cheerful alternative to\n+> Hangman. It is intended as a slightly more adventurous \"Hello World\" project\n+> for testing AI-assisted software development. The game includes input\n+> validation, state management, a simple loop, win/loss conditions, and a\n+> friendly terminal interface.\n+\n+Guess the hidden word before the garden runs out of water. Each correct guess\n+helps the garden grow; each wrong guess costs a drop of water and lets a weed\n+appear. Reveal the whole word to make the garden bloom — it's like Hangman,\n+but with plants instead of gallows.\n+\n+## Requirements\n+\n+- Python 3.11 or newer (standard library only — nothing to install).\n+\n+## How to run\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m word_garden\n+```\n+\n+Options:\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty easy    # easy | normal | hard (default: normal)\n+python3 -m word_garden --ascii              # pure-ASCII display for terminals without emoji\n+```\n+\n+`--difficulty` changes both the starting water and the pool of words:\n+\n+| Difficulty | Water | Word length |\n+|---|---:|---:|\n+| easy   | 8 | 4–6 letters |\n+| normal | 6 | 5–8 letters |\n+| hard   | 4 | 7+ letters  |\n+\n+## How to play\n+\n+1. The game picks a secret word and shows one blank per letter.\n+2. Type a single letter and press Enter at the `Guess a letter:` prompt.\n+3. A correct guess reveals every matching position in the word.\n+4. A wrong guess costs one unit of water and adds one weed.\n+5. Repeated or invalid input (empty, multiple characters, digits, symbols)\n+   is rejected with a friendly message and does **not** cost a turn.\n+6. You win when the whole word is revealed; you lose if water reaches zero\n+   first. Press Ctrl-D or Ctrl-C at any time to leave the garden cleanly.\n+\n+## Sample screen\n+\n+```text\n+🌱 Word Garden\n+\n+Garden:  🌿  The garden is growing.\n+Word:    G _ R _ E _\n+Guessed: A E G R\n+Water:   4/6 💧💧💧💧\n+Weeds:   2 🌿🌿\n+\n+Good guess! The garden grows.\n+\n+Guess a letter:\n+```\n+\n+The same turn in `--ascii` mode:\n+\n+```text\n+Word Garden\n+\n+Garden:  **  The garden is growing.\n+Word:    G _ R _ E _\n+Guessed: A E G R\n+Water:   4/6 [****  ]\n+Weeds:   2 [--]\n+\n+Good guess! The garden grows.\n+\n+Guess a letter:\n+```\n+\n+## Project layout\n+\n+```text\n+word_garden/\n+  __main__.py   # python3 -m word_garden entry point\n+  main.py       # argument parsing and the game loop (the only I/O module)\n+  game.py       # game state, guesses, win/loss logic\n+  words.py      # word list and difficulty filtering\n+  ui.py         # pure rendering (returns strings; no printing)\n+tests/          # unittest suite (engine + UI)\n+```\n+\n+## Running the tests\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests\n+```\ndiff --git a/tests/test_ui.py b/tests/test_ui.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..774d9dd\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_ui.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,290 @@\n+import unittest\n+from unittest import mock\n+\n+from word_garden.game import GameState\n+from word_garden import main as main_module\n+from word_garden.main import GOODBYE, PROMPT, main\n+from word_garden.ui import (\n+    GROWTH_STAGES,\n+    LOSS_BODY,\n+    LOSS_HEADER,\n+    LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE,\n+    STAGE_LOSS,\n+    STAGE_NEAR_WIN,\n+    STAGE_PROGRESS,\n+    STAGE_START,\n+    STAGE_WIN,\n+    WATER_EMOJI,\n+    WEED_EMOJI,\n+    WIN_BODY,\n+    WIN_HEADER,\n+    WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE,\n+    growth_stage,\n+    loss_screen,\n+    render,\n+    win_screen,\n+)\n+\n+\n+def _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n+    \"\"\"Build a GameState directly with pinned values (no randomness).\"\"\"\n+    defaults = dict(\n+        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+        guessed_letters=set(),\n+        remaining_water=6,\n+        weed_count=0,\n+        max_water=6,\n+    )\n+    defaults.update(kwargs)\n+    return GameState(**defaults)\n+\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# render — emoji mode\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+class TestRenderEmoji(unittest.TestCase):\n+    def test_contains_title_and_word_and_guesses(self):\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"R\"})\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Word Garden\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"G _ R _ _ _\", out)\n+        # Guessed letters sorted and space-separated.\n+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"G R\", out)\n+\n+    def test_water_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6)\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(WATER_EMOJI * 4, out)\n+\n+    def test_weeds_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n+        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"2\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(WEED_EMOJI * 2, out)\n+\n+    def test_status_message_shown_when_present(self):\n+        state = _make_state(status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\")\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"No match. A weed appears.\", out)\n+\n+    def test_empty_status_message_not_rendered_as_blank_feedback(self):\n+        # A fresh game has no feedback line; the last line is the weeds row.\n+        state = _make_state()\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertTrue(out.rstrip().endswith(render(state).splitlines()[-1]))\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"None\", out)\n+\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# render — ASCII mode (must be pure ASCII)\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+class TestRenderAscii(unittest.TestCase):\n+    def test_output_is_pure_ascii(self):\n+        state = _make_state(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"Z\"},\n+            remaining_water=5,\n+            weed_count=1,\n+            status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\",\n+        )\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertTrue(out.isascii(), f\"non-ASCII characters found: {out!r}\")\n+\n+    def test_ascii_has_labels_count_and_no_emoji(self):\n+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6, weed_count=2)\n+        out = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", out)\n+        self.assertNotIn(WATER_EMOJI, out)\n+        self.assertNotIn(WEED_EMOJI, out)\n+\n+    def test_ascii_win_loss_screens_pure_ascii(self):\n+        won = _make_state(\n+            guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"), game_over=True, won=True\n+        )\n+        lost = _make_state(remaining_water=0, weed_count=6, game_over=True)\n+        self.assertTrue(win_screen(won, ascii_mode=True).isascii())\n+        self.assertTrue(loss_screen(lost, ascii_mode=True).isascii())\n+\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# growth stages (SPEC §10): start / progress / near-win / win / loss\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+class TestGrowthStages(unittest.TestCase):\n+    def test_start_when_nothing_revealed(self):\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_START)\n+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_START][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n+\n+    def test_progress_when_some_revealed(self):\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\"})\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_PROGRESS)\n+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_PROGRESS][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n+\n+    def test_near_win_when_one_letter_left(self):\n+        # GARDEN with all but N revealed → exactly one secret letter remains.\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"})\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_NEAR_WIN)\n+        self.assertIn(GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_NEAR_WIN][\"emoji\"], render(state))\n+\n+    def test_win_stage_when_won(self):\n+        state = _make_state(guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"), game_over=True, won=True)\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_WIN)\n+\n+    def test_loss_stage_when_lost(self):\n+        state = _make_state(remaining_water=0, weed_count=6, game_over=True, won=False)\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_LOSS)\n+\n+    def test_wrong_guesses_alone_do_not_count_as_progress(self):\n+        # Only wrong letters guessed → no secret letter revealed → still start.\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"Z\", \"Q\"})\n+        self.assertEqual(growth_stage(state), STAGE_START)\n+\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# win / loss screens (SPEC §6.6 / §6.7)\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+class TestEndScreens(unittest.TestCase):\n+    def test_win_screen_names_word_and_message(self):\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set(\"GARDEN\"),\n+                            game_over=True, won=True)\n+        out = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, out)\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), out)\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"GARDEN\", out)\n+\n+    def test_loss_screen_reveals_secret_word(self):\n+        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"PLANET\", remaining_water=0, weed_count=4,\n+                            game_over=True, won=False)\n+        out = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER, out)\n+        self.assertIn(LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"PLANET\"), out)\n+        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, out)\n+        self.assertIn(\"PLANET\", out)\n+\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# end-to-end main() runs with injected I/O\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+class _Recorder:\n+    \"\"\"Collects output_fn calls; serves scripted input_fn responses.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def __init__(self, inputs):\n+        self._inputs = iter(inputs)\n+        self.outputs: list[str] = []\n+\n+    def input_fn(self, prompt=\"\"):\n+        return next(self._inputs)\n+\n+    def output_fn(self, text=\"\"):\n+        self.outputs.append(str(text))\n+\n+    @property\n+    def text(self) -> str:\n+        return \"\\n\".join(self.outputs)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainEndToEnd(unittest.TestCase):\n+    def test_full_win_shows_win_screen(self):\n+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            code = main([\"--difficulty\", \"normal\"],\n+                        input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, rec.text)\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), rec.text)\n+\n+    def test_full_loss_shows_loss_screen_with_word(self):\n+        # Six wrong guesses (none in GARDEN) exhaust the normal water of 6.\n+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            code = main([\"--difficulty\", \"normal\"],\n+                        input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n+        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER, rec.text)\n+        self.assertIn(LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"), rec.text)\n+\n+    def test_invalid_input_reprompts_without_consuming_water(self):\n+        # Two invalid inputs, then win. Game still won → invalids cost no turn.\n+        rec = _Recorder([\"\", \"7\", \"!\"] + list(\"GARDEN\"))\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            code = main([], input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n+        # Validation messages surfaced.\n+        self.assertIn(\"Please enter a single letter.\", rec.text)\n+        self.assertIn(\"That is not a letter.\", rec.text)\n+        # And the game still reached the win screen.\n+        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER, rec.text)\n+\n+    def test_ascii_mode_run_is_pure_ascii(self):\n+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            main([\"--ascii\"], input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n+        self.assertTrue(rec.text.isascii(), f\"non-ASCII in output: {rec.text!r}\")\n+\n+    def test_difficulty_easy_sets_water_to_eight(self):\n+        # First rendered frame should show the easy starting water of 8/8.\n+        rec = _Recorder(list(\"GARDEN\"))\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"],\n+                 input_fn=rec.input_fn, output_fn=rec.output_fn)\n+        self.assertIn(\"8/8\", rec.outputs[0])\n+\n+    def test_eof_exits_cleanly_with_goodbye(self):\n+        def eof_input(prompt=\"\"):\n+            raise EOFError\n+\n+        outputs = []\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            code = main([], input_fn=eof_input, output_fn=lambda t=\"\": outputs.append(str(t)))\n+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n+        self.assertIn(GOODBYE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n+\n+    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exits_cleanly_with_goodbye(self):\n+        def interrupt_input(prompt=\"\"):\n+            raise KeyboardInterrupt\n+\n+        outputs = []\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            code = main([], input_fn=interrupt_input,\n+                        output_fn=lambda t=\"\": outputs.append(str(t)))\n+        self.assertEqual(code, 0)\n+        self.assertIn(GOODBYE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n+\n+    def test_help_exits_zero(self):\n+        with self.assertRaises(SystemExit) as ctx:\n+            main([\"--help\"], input_fn=lambda p=\"\": \"\", output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n+        self.assertEqual(ctx.exception.code, 0)\n+\n+    def test_bad_difficulty_exits_two(self):\n+        with self.assertRaises(SystemExit) as ctx:\n+            main([\"--difficulty\", \"impossible\"],\n+                 input_fn=lambda p=\"\": \"\", output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n+        self.assertEqual(ctx.exception.code, 2)\n+\n+    def test_prompt_text_is_passed_to_input(self):\n+        seen = []\n+\n+        def capture_input(prompt=\"\"):\n+            seen.append(prompt)\n+            return next(letters)\n+\n+        letters = iter(\"GARDEN\")\n+        with mock.patch(\"word_garden.words.select_word\", return_value=\"GARDEN\"):\n+            main([], input_fn=capture_input, output_fn=lambda t=\"\": None)\n+        self.assertEqual(seen[0], PROMPT)\n+\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    unittest.main()\ndiff --git a/word_garden/__main__.py b/word_garden/__main__.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..cc88885\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/__main__.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+\"\"\"Allow ``python3 -m word_garden`` to launch the game.\"\"\"\n+\n+from .main import main\n+\n+raise SystemExit(main())\ndiff --git a/word_garden/main.py b/word_garden/main.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..2b11073\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/main.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\n+\"\"\"Command-line entry point and game loop for Word Garden.\n+\n+This is the ONLY module that touches stdin/stdout. All terminal interaction\n+goes through the injectable ``input_fn``/``output_fn`` so the loop is testable\n+without a real terminal.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+import argparse\n+\n+from .game import apply_guess, new_game, validate_guess\n+from .ui import loss_screen, render, win_screen\n+\n+PROMPT = \"Guess a letter: \"\n+GOODBYE = \"Thanks for visiting the garden. Come back soon!\"\n+\n+_DIFFICULTIES = [\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"]\n+\n+\n+def _build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n+    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n+        prog=\"word_garden\",\n+        description=\"Word Garden — a friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n+    )\n+    parser.add_argument(\n+        \"--difficulty\",\n+        choices=_DIFFICULTIES,\n+        default=\"normal\",\n+        help=\"word length and starting water (default: normal).\",\n+    )\n+    parser.add_argument(\n+        \"--ascii\",\n+        action=\"store_true\",\n+        help=\"use the pure-ASCII display instead of emoji.\",\n+    )\n+    return parser\n+\n+\n+def main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Run a full game and return the process exit code (0).\n+\n+    ``input_fn`` and ``output_fn`` default to the builtins but may be injected\n+    for testing. Note: ``parse_args`` is intentionally NOT wrapped in\n+    try/except — ``--help`` must exit 0 and a usage error must exit 2.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    args = _build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n+    ascii_mode = args.ascii\n+    state = new_game(args.difficulty)\n+\n+    try:\n+        while not state.game_over:\n+            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode))\n+            output_fn(\"\")\n+            raw = input_fn(PROMPT)\n+            letter, error = validate_guess(raw)\n+            if letter is None:\n+                # Invalid input: show the message and re-prompt without\n+                # consuming a turn (SPEC §6.2/§14).\n+                output_fn(error)\n+                continue\n+            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n+\n+        screen = (\n+            win_screen(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode)\n+            if state.won\n+            else loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=ascii_mode)\n+        )\n+        output_fn(screen)\n+        return 0\n+    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n+        # Ctrl-D / Ctrl-C: friendly goodbye, clean exit, never a traceback.\n+        output_fn(\"\")\n+        output_fn(GOODBYE)\n+        return 0\ndiff --git a/word_garden/ui.py b/word_garden/ui.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..bb37e31\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/ui.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,160 @@\n+\"\"\"Pure rendering for Word Garden.\n+\n+Every function in this module returns a string. There is deliberately no\n+``print()``/``input()`` here — all I/O lives in :mod:`word_garden.main`.\n+Both an emoji display and a pure-ASCII fallback (SPEC §10, §18) are supported.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from .game import GameState, display_word\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# Growth-stage visuals (SPEC §10).\n+#\n+# Single source of truth: each stage maps to its emoji glyph, its ASCII\n+# fallback glyph (no non-ASCII characters), and a friendly text label. The\n+# render status line, the win screen, and the loss screen all read from here\n+# so the table is never duplicated.\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+STAGE_START = \"start\"\n+STAGE_PROGRESS = \"progress\"\n+STAGE_NEAR_WIN = \"near_win\"\n+STAGE_WIN = \"win\"\n+STAGE_LOSS = \"loss\"\n+\n+GROWTH_STAGES: dict[str, dict[str, str]] = {\n+    STAGE_START:    {\"emoji\": \"🌱\", \"ascii\": \"*\",    \"label\": \"A seedling sprouts.\"},\n+    STAGE_PROGRESS: {\"emoji\": \"🌿\", \"ascii\": \"**\",   \"label\": \"The garden is growing.\"},\n+    STAGE_NEAR_WIN: {\"emoji\": \"🌷\", \"ascii\": \"***\",  \"label\": \"Buds are about to bloom.\"},\n+    STAGE_WIN:      {\"emoji\": \"🌻\", \"ascii\": \"\\\\o/\",  \"label\": \"Bloom!\"},\n+    STAGE_LOSS:     {\"emoji\": \"🥀\", \"ascii\": \"x_x\",  \"label\": \"Wilted.\"},\n+}\n+\n+# Resource symbols (SPEC §10).\n+WATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\n+WEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n+WATER_ASCII = \"*\"\n+WEED_ASCII = \"-\"\n+\n+# Layout: label column width shared by every row of the status block.\n+_LABEL_WIDTH = 9\n+\n+# Title (SPEC §5/§9). The title always shows the seedling glyph; the dynamic\n+# growth stage is shown on its own \"Garden:\" line below.\n+TITLE_TEXT = \"Word Garden\"\n+\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+# End-screen message strings (SPEC §6.6 win / §6.7 loss).\n+#\n+# These are screen-layout strings owned by the UI, distinct from the engine's\n+# one-line ``status_message`` constants. Defined once here; tests import them.\n+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n+\n+WIN_HEADER = \"Bloom!\"\n+WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE = \"You guessed the word: {word}\"\n+WIN_BODY = \"The garden is thriving.\"\n+\n+LOSS_HEADER = \"The garden ran out of water.\"\n+LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE = \"The word was: {word}\"\n+LOSS_BODY = \"Try again and grow a new garden.\"\n+\n+\n+def growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Return the growth-stage key for ``state`` (a key of GROWTH_STAGES).\n+\n+    Driven by progress per SPEC §10: a terminal state is win or loss; before\n+    that it is start (nothing revealed), near-win (one secret letter left),\n+    or progress (something revealed but more than one letter remains).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    if state.game_over and state.won:\n+        return STAGE_WIN\n+    if state.game_over:\n+        return STAGE_LOSS\n+    secret_letters = set(state.secret_word)\n+    revealed = secret_letters & state.guessed_letters\n+    if not revealed:\n+        return STAGE_START\n+    if len(secret_letters - state.guessed_letters) <= 1:\n+        return STAGE_NEAR_WIN\n+    return STAGE_PROGRESS\n+\n+\n+def _glyph(stage: str, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n+    return GROWTH_STAGES[stage][\"ascii\" if ascii_mode else \"emoji\"]\n+\n+\n+def _label(text: str, value: str) -> str:\n+    return f\"{text:<{_LABEL_WIDTH}}{value}\".rstrip()\n+\n+\n+def _water_line(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Water row with text label AND count AND symbols (SPEC §18).\"\"\"\n+    count = f\"{state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water}\"\n+    if ascii_mode:\n+        used = state.max_water - state.remaining_water\n+        symbols = \"[\" + WATER_ASCII * state.remaining_water + \" \" * used + \"]\"\n+    else:\n+        symbols = WATER_EMOJI * state.remaining_water\n+    return _label(\"Water:\", f\"{count} {symbols}\")\n+\n+\n+def _weeds_line(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Weeds row with text label AND count AND symbols (SPEC §18).\"\"\"\n+    count = str(state.weed_count)\n+    if ascii_mode:\n+        symbols = \"[\" + WEED_ASCII * state.weed_count + \"]\"\n+    else:\n+        symbols = WEED_EMOJI * state.weed_count\n+    return _label(\"Weeds:\", f\"{count} {symbols}\")\n+\n+\n+def render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Return the full turn display (SPEC §9), as a string.\n+\n+    Order: title, garden/plant status, masked word, guessed letters, water,\n+    weeds, then the previous turn's ``status_message`` (omitted when empty).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    stage = growth_stage(state)\n+    if ascii_mode:\n+        title = TITLE_TEXT\n+    else:\n+        title = f\"{GROWTH_STAGES[STAGE_START]['emoji']} {TITLE_TEXT}\"\n+\n+    garden_value = f\"{_glyph(stage, ascii_mode)}  {GROWTH_STAGES[stage]['label']}\"\n+    guessed = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters))\n+\n+    lines = [\n+        title,\n+        \"\",\n+        _label(\"Garden:\", garden_value),\n+        _label(\"Word:\", display_word(state)),\n+        _label(\"Guessed:\", guessed),\n+        _water_line(state, ascii_mode),\n+        _weeds_line(state, ascii_mode),\n+    ]\n+    if state.status_message:\n+        lines.append(\"\")\n+        lines.append(state.status_message)\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n+\n+\n+def win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Return the winning end screen (SPEC §6.6); names the secret word.\"\"\"\n+    lines = [\n+        f\"{_glyph(STAGE_WIN, ascii_mode)} {WIN_HEADER}\",\n+        \"\",\n+        WIN_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=state.secret_word),\n+        WIN_BODY,\n+    ]\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n+\n+\n+def loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Return the losing end screen (SPEC §6.7); reveals the secret word.\"\"\"\n+    lines = [\n+        f\"{_glyph(STAGE_LOSS, ascii_mode)} {LOSS_HEADER}\",\n+        \"\",\n+        LOSS_REVEAL_TEMPLATE.format(word=state.secret_word),\n+        LOSS_BODY,\n+    ]\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n","numLines":657,"startLine":1,"totalLines":657}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01DdJcxVoQv2e2XaPuwypQCE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015BET9f4Nn4WgwdZerQrdwU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates/B.diff"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":40450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"3d7cceda-6866-47e0-ba77-cbfa81a7dfe6","request_id":"req_011CbxgrJHAxfCzQN6YdLYaW"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015BET9f4Nn4WgwdZerQrdwU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tdiff --git a/README.md b/README.md\n2\tnew file mode 100644\n3\tindex 0000000..49153b9\n4\t--- /dev/null\n5\t+++ b/README.md\n6\t@@ -0,0 +1,80 @@\n7\t+# Word Garden\n8\t+\n9\t+A friendly terminal word-guessing game. Guess the hidden word before the garden runs out of water. It is like Hangman, but with plants instead of gallows.\n10\t+\n11\t+Word Garden is a small TUI game designed as a more cheerful alternative to Hangman. It is intended as a slightly more adventurous \"Hello World\" project for testing AI-assisted software development. The game includes input validation, state management, a simple loop, win/loss conditions, and a friendly terminal interface.\n12\t+\n13\t+## How to Play\n14\t+\n15\t+Start the game:\n16\t+\n17\t+```bash\n18\t+python3 -m word_garden\n19\t+```\n20\t+\n21\t+The game will display a masked word and prompt you for a letter guess. Each correct guess reveals matching letters and helps your garden grow. Each incorrect guess costs water and allows weeds to spread.\n22\t+\n23\t+Win by revealing all the letters before the garden runs out of water.\n24\t+\n25\t+## Options\n26\t+\n27\t+**Difficulty levels:**\n28\t+\n29\t+```bash\n30\t+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty easy      # 8 water, 4–6 letter words\n31\t+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty normal    # 6 water, 5–8 letter words (default)\n32\t+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty hard      # 4 water, 7+ letter words\n33\t+```\n34\t+\n35\t+**ASCII mode (no emoji):**\n36\t+\n37\t+```bash\n38\t+python3 -m word_garden --ascii\n39\t+```\n40\t+\n41\t+## Rules\n42\t+\n43\t+- The game picks a random secret word.\n44\t+- You guess one letter at a time.\n45\t+- A correct guess reveals all matching positions and helps your plant grow.\n46\t+- An incorrect guess costs one water and adds a weed.\n47\t+- You win by revealing the entire word.\n48\t+- You lose if the garden runs out of water before the word is complete.\n49\t+\n50\t+## Example Game\n51\t+\n52\t+```\n53\t+🌱 Word Garden\n54\t+\n55\t+Word:     _ _ _ _ _ _\n56\t+Guessed:\n57\t+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧💧\n58\t+Weeds:\n59\t+\n60\t+Guess a letter: a\n61\t+\n62\t+Good guess! The garden grows.\n63\t+\n64\t+Word:     _ A _ _ _ _\n65\t+Guessed:  A\n66\t+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧💧\n67\t+Weeds:\n68\t+\n69\t+Guess a letter: z\n70\t+\n71\t+No match. A weed appears.\n72\t+\n73\t+Word:     _ A _ _ _ _\n74\t+Guessed:  A Z\n75\t+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧\n76\t+Weeds:   🌿\n77\t+```\n78\t+\n79\t+## Accessibility\n80\t+\n81\t+The game supports both emoji and ASCII modes. In ASCII mode, water and weeds are shown as counts with text labels, so the game is fully playable without emoji support.\n82\t+\n83\t+```\n84\t+Water: 5/6 [*****]\n85\t+Weeds: 1 [-]\n86\t+```\n87\tdiff --git a/tests/test_ui.py b/tests/test_ui.py\n88\tnew file mode 100644\n89\tindex 0000000..fff5e7b\n90\t--- /dev/null\n91\t+++ b/tests/test_ui.py\n92\t@@ -0,0 +1,360 @@\n93\t+import random\n94\t+import unittest\n95\t+from io import StringIO\n96\t+\n97\t+from word_garden.game import GameState, new_game\n98\t+from word_garden.ui import render, win_screen, loss_screen\n99\t+from word_garden.main import main\n100\t+\n101\t+\n102\t+class TestRender(unittest.TestCase):\n103\t+    \"\"\"Test the render() function for both emoji and ASCII modes.\"\"\"\n104\t+\n105\t+    def test_render_emoji_at_start(self):\n106\t+        \"\"\"Emoji render includes title, word, water, weeds, growth glyph.\"\"\"\n107\t+        state = GameState(\n108\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n109\t+            guessed_letters=set(),\n110\t+            remaining_water=6,\n111\t+            weed_count=0,\n112\t+            max_water=6,\n113\t+            status_message=\"\",\n114\t+            game_over=False,\n115\t+            won=False,\n116\t+        )\n117\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n118\t+        self.assertIn(\"🌱 Word Garden\", output)\n119\t+        self.assertIn(\"_ _ _ _ _ _\", output)\n120\t+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", output)\n121\t+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 6/6 💧💧💧💧💧💧\", output)\n122\t+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 0\", output)\n123\t+\n124\t+    def test_render_emoji_with_guesses(self):\n125\t+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows guessed letters sorted.\"\"\"\n126\t+        state = GameState(\n127\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n128\t+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"E\"},\n129\t+            remaining_water=6,\n130\t+            weed_count=0,\n131\t+            max_water=6,\n132\t+            status_message=\"Good guess!\",\n133\t+            game_over=False,\n134\t+            won=False,\n135\t+        )\n136\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n137\t+        self.assertIn(\"_ A R _ E _\", output)\n138\t+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:  A E R\", output)\n139\t+        self.assertIn(\"Good guess!\", output)\n140\t+\n141\t+    def test_render_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n142\t+        \"\"\"ASCII render contains no emoji characters.\"\"\"\n143\t+        state = GameState(\n144\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n145\t+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\"},\n146\t+            remaining_water=4,\n147\t+            weed_count=2,\n148\t+            max_water=6,\n149\t+            status_message=\"\",\n150\t+            game_over=False,\n151\t+            won=False,\n152\t+        )\n153\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n154\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output)\n155\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output)\n156\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output)\n157\t+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 4/6 [****]\", output)\n158\t+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 2 [--]\", output)\n159\t+        self.assertIn(\"*\", output)  # ASCII plant\n160\t+\n161\t+    def test_render_emoji_progress_stage(self):\n162\t+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows progress glyph when some letters guessed.\"\"\"\n163\t+        state = GameState(\n164\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n165\t+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"D\"},\n166\t+            remaining_water=6,\n167\t+            weed_count=0,\n168\t+            max_water=6,\n169\t+            status_message=\"\",\n170\t+            game_over=False,\n171\t+            won=False,\n172\t+        )\n173\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n174\t+        self.assertIn(\"🌿 Word Garden\", output)\n175\t+\n176\t+    def test_render_emoji_near_win_stage(self):\n177\t+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows near-win glyph when almost all letters guessed.\"\"\"\n178\t+        state = GameState(\n179\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n180\t+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"},\n181\t+            remaining_water=6,\n182\t+            weed_count=0,\n183\t+            max_water=6,\n184\t+            status_message=\"\",\n185\t+            game_over=False,\n186\t+            won=False,\n187\t+        )\n188\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n189\t+        self.assertIn(\"🌷 Word Garden\", output)\n190\t+\n191\t+    def test_render_with_status_message(self):\n192\t+        \"\"\"Render includes status message on its own line.\"\"\"\n193\t+        state = GameState(\n194\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n195\t+            guessed_letters=set(),\n196\t+            remaining_water=6,\n197\t+            weed_count=0,\n198\t+            max_water=6,\n199\t+            status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\",\n200\t+            game_over=False,\n201\t+            won=False,\n202\t+        )\n203\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n204\t+        self.assertIn(\"No match. A weed appears.\", output)\n205\t+\n206\t+    def test_render_ascii_water_count(self):\n207\t+        \"\"\"ASCII mode shows water count with label.\"\"\"\n208\t+        state = GameState(\n209\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n210\t+            guessed_letters=set(),\n211\t+            remaining_water=3,\n212\t+            weed_count=0,\n213\t+            max_water=6,\n214\t+            status_message=\"\",\n215\t+            game_over=False,\n216\t+            won=False,\n217\t+        )\n218\t+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n219\t+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 3/6\", output)\n220\t+\n221\t+\n222\t+class TestWinScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n223\t+    \"\"\"Test the win_screen() function.\"\"\"\n224\t+\n225\t+    def test_win_screen_emoji(self):\n226\t+        \"\"\"Win screen shows bloom emoji, word, and thriving message.\"\"\"\n227\t+        state = GameState(\n228\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n229\t+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n230\t+            remaining_water=6,\n231\t+            weed_count=0,\n232\t+            max_water=6,\n233\t+            status_message=\"You guessed the word: GARDEN. The garden is thriving.\",\n234\t+            game_over=True,\n235\t+            won=True,\n236\t+        )\n237\t+        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n238\t+        self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output)\n239\t+        self.assertIn(\"You guessed the word: GARDEN\", output)\n240\t+        self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output)\n241\t+\n242\t+    def test_win_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n243\t+        \"\"\"Win screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n244\t+        state = GameState(\n245\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n246\t+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n247\t+            remaining_water=6,\n248\t+            weed_count=0,\n249\t+            max_water=6,\n250\t+            status_message=\"\",\n251\t+            game_over=True,\n252\t+            won=True,\n253\t+        )\n254\t+        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n255\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output)\n256\t+        self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output)\n257\t+\n258\t+\n259\t+class TestLossScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n260\t+    \"\"\"Test the loss_screen() function.\"\"\"\n261\t+\n262\t+    def test_loss_screen_emoji(self):\n263\t+        \"\"\"Loss screen shows wilted emoji, word, and try-again message.\"\"\"\n264\t+        state = GameState(\n265\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n266\t+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n267\t+            remaining_water=0,\n268\t+            weed_count=6,\n269\t+            max_water=6,\n270\t+            status_message=\"The garden ran out of water. The word was: GARDEN.\",\n271\t+            game_over=True,\n272\t+            won=False,\n273\t+        )\n274\t+        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n275\t+        self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n276\t+        self.assertIn(\"The word was: GARDEN\", output)\n277\t+        self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output)\n278\t+\n279\t+    def test_loss_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n280\t+        \"\"\"Loss screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n281\t+        state = GameState(\n282\t+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n283\t+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n284\t+            remaining_water=0,\n285\t+            weed_count=6,\n286\t+            max_water=6,\n287\t+            status_message=\"\",\n288\t+            game_over=True,\n289\t+            won=False,\n290\t+        )\n291\t+        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n292\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🥀\", output)\n293\t+        self.assertIn(\"* The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n294\t+\n295\t+\n296\t+class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n297\t+    \"\"\"Test main() game loop completes successfully.\"\"\"\n298\t+\n299\t+    def test_end_to_end_with_all_alphabet(self):\n300\t+        \"\"\"E2E: game runs and completes with all alphabet guesses.\"\"\"\n301\t+        outputs = []\n302\t+\n303\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n304\t+            outputs.append(text)\n305\t+\n306\t+        guesses = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n307\t+        guess_index = [0]\n308\t+\n309\t+        def fake_input():\n310\t+            if guess_index[0] >= len(guesses):\n311\t+                raise EOFError()\n312\t+            letter = guesses[guess_index[0]]\n313\t+            guess_index[0] += 1\n314\t+            return letter\n315\t+\n316\t+        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n317\t+\n318\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n319\t+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n320\t+        self.assertIn(\"Word Garden\", output_str)\n321\t+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", output_str)\n322\t+        self.assertTrue(output_str.count(\"Bloom!\") > 0 or output_str.count(\"The garden ran out of water\") > 0)\n323\t+\n324\t+    def test_end_to_end_ascii_mode(self):\n325\t+        \"\"\"E2E: game in ASCII mode uses no emoji.\"\"\"\n326\t+        outputs = []\n327\t+\n328\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n329\t+            outputs.append(text)\n330\t+\n331\t+        guesses = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n332\t+        guess_index = [0]\n333\t+\n334\t+        def fake_input():\n335\t+            if guess_index[0] >= len(guesses):\n336\t+                raise EOFError()\n337\t+            letter = guesses[guess_index[0]]\n338\t+            guess_index[0] += 1\n339\t+            return letter\n340\t+\n341\t+        result = main([\"--ascii\", \"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n342\t+\n343\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n344\t+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n345\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n346\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n347\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🥀\", output_str)\n348\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output_str)\n349\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output_str)\n350\t+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌷\", output_str)\n351\t+\n352\t+\n353\t+class TestMainEndToEndLoss(unittest.TestCase):\n354\t+    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a loss.\"\"\"\n355\t+\n356\t+    def test_end_to_end_loss(self):\n357\t+        \"\"\"E2E: scripted loss game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n358\t+        outputs = []\n359\t+\n360\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n361\t+            outputs.append(text)\n362\t+\n363\t+        def fake_input_gen():\n364\t+            wrong_letters = \"ZYXWVUTSRQPON\"\n365\t+            for letter in wrong_letters:\n366\t+                yield letter\n367\t+\n368\t+        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n369\t+\n370\t+        def fake_input():\n371\t+            try:\n372\t+                letter = next(inputs)\n373\t+                return letter\n374\t+            except StopIteration:\n375\t+                raise EOFError()\n376\t+\n377\t+        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n378\t+\n379\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n380\t+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n381\t+        self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output_str)\n382\t+        self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output_str)\n383\t+\n384\t+\n385\t+class TestMainInvalidInputRePrompt(unittest.TestCase):\n386\t+    \"\"\"Test that invalid input re-prompts without consuming a turn.\"\"\"\n387\t+\n388\t+    def test_invalid_then_valid(self):\n389\t+        \"\"\"Invalid input should re-prompt; valid input should advance.\"\"\"\n390\t+        rng = random.Random(42)\n391\t+        state = new_game(\"normal\", rng=rng)\n392\t+\n393\t+        guesses = [\"\", \"A\"] + sorted(state.secret_word)[1:]\n394\t+\n395\t+        outputs = []\n396\t+        guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n397\t+\n398\t+        def fake_input():\n399\t+            try:\n400\t+                return next(guess_iter)\n401\t+            except StopIteration:\n402\t+                raise EOFError()\n403\t+\n404\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n405\t+            outputs.append(text + end)\n406\t+\n407\t+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n408\t+\n409\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n410\t+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n411\t+        self.assertIn(\"Please enter a single letter.\", output_str)\n412\t+        self.assertIn(\"Good guess! The garden grows.\", output_str)\n413\t+\n414\t+\n415\t+class TestMainEOFGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n416\t+    \"\"\"Test that EOF (Ctrl-D) exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n417\t+\n418\t+    def test_eof_exit_code(self):\n419\t+        \"\"\"EOF should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n420\t+        outputs = []\n421\t+\n422\t+        def fake_input():\n423\t+            raise EOFError()\n424\t+\n425\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n426\t+            outputs.append(text + end)\n427\t+\n428\t+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n429\t+\n430\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n431\t+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n432\t+        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\n433\t+\n434\t+\n435\t+class TestMainKeyboardInterruptGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n436\t+    \"\"\"Test that Ctrl-C exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n437\t+\n438\t+    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exit_code(self):\n439\t+        \"\"\"KeyboardInterrupt should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n440\t+        outputs = []\n441\t+\n442\t+        def fake_input():\n443\t+            raise KeyboardInterrupt()\n444\t+\n445\t+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n446\t+            outputs.append(text + end)\n447\t+\n448\t+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n449\t+\n450\t+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n451\t+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n452\t+        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\n453\tdiff --git a/word_garden/__main__.py b/word_garden/__main__.py\n454\tnew file mode 100644\n455\tindex 0000000..70ba871\n456\t--- /dev/null\n457\t+++ b/word_garden/__main__.py\n458\t@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n459\t+import sys\n460\t+from .main import main\n461\t+\n462\t+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n463\t+    sys.exit(main())\n464\tdiff --git a/word_garden/main.py b/word_garden/main.py\n465\tnew file mode 100644\n466\tindex 0000000..eeb1943\n467\t--- /dev/null\n468\t+++ b/word_garden/main.py\n469\t@@ -0,0 +1,66 @@\n470\t+import argparse\n471\t+import sys\n472\t+\n473\t+from .game import new_game, validate_guess, apply_guess\n474\t+from .ui import render, win_screen, loss_screen\n475\t+\n476\t+\n477\t+def main(argv=None, input_fn=None, output_fn=None) -> int:\n478\t+    \"\"\"Run the Word Garden game loop.\n479\t+\n480\t+    Args:\n481\t+        argv: Command-line arguments (default: sys.argv[1:])\n482\t+        input_fn: Injectable input function (default: input)\n483\t+        output_fn: Injectable output function (default: print)\n484\t+\n485\t+    Returns:\n486\t+        Exit code (0 on success or EOF/interrupt)\n487\t+    \"\"\"\n488\t+    if input_fn is None:\n489\t+        input_fn = input\n490\t+    if output_fn is None:\n491\t+        output_fn = print\n492\t+\n493\t+    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n494\t+        prog=\"word_garden\",\n495\t+        description=\"A friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n496\t+    )\n497\t+    parser.add_argument(\n498\t+        \"--difficulty\",\n499\t+        choices=[\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"],\n500\t+        default=\"normal\",\n501\t+        help=\"Game difficulty (default: normal)\",\n502\t+    )\n503\t+    parser.add_argument(\n504\t+        \"--ascii\",\n505\t+        action=\"store_true\",\n506\t+        help=\"Use ASCII-only output (no emoji)\",\n507\t+    )\n508\t+\n509\t+    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n510\t+\n511\t+    state = new_game(args.difficulty)\n512\t+\n513\t+    try:\n514\t+        while not state.game_over:\n515\t+            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n516\t+            output_fn(\"Guess a letter: \", end=\"\")\n517\t+            user_input = input_fn()\n518\t+\n519\t+            letter, error = validate_guess(user_input)\n520\t+            if error:\n521\t+                output_fn(error)\n522\t+                continue\n523\t+\n524\t+            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n525\t+\n526\t+        if state.won:\n527\t+            output_fn(win_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n528\t+        else:\n529\t+            output_fn(loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n530\t+\n531\t+        return 0\n532\t+\n533\t+    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n534\t+        output_fn(\"\\nThanks for playing! Goodbye.\")\n535\t+        return 0\n536\tdiff --git a/word_garden/ui.py b/word_garden/ui.py\n537\tnew file mode 100644\n538\tindex 0000000..fb1c250\n539\t--- /dev/null\n540\t+++ b/word_garden/ui.py\n541\t@@ -0,0 +1,106 @@\n542\t+from .game import GameState, display_word\n543\t+\n544\t+# Growth stage glyphs\n545\t+_GROWTH_EMOJI = {\n546\t+    \"start\": \"🌱\",\n547\t+    \"progress\": \"🌿\",\n548\t+    \"near_win\": \"🌷\",\n549\t+    \"win\": \"🌻\",\n550\t+    \"loss\": \"🥀\",\n551\t+}\n552\t+\n553\t+_GROWTH_ASCII = {\n554\t+    \"start\": \"*\",\n555\t+    \"progress\": \"*\",\n556\t+    \"near_win\": \"*\",\n557\t+    \"win\": \"*\",\n558\t+    \"loss\": \"*\",\n559\t+}\n560\t+\n561\t+_WATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\n562\t+_WATER_ASCII = \"*\"\n563\t+\n564\t+_WEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n565\t+_WEED_ASCII = \"-\"\n566\t+\n567\t+\n568\t+def _growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n569\t+    \"\"\"Determine the current growth stage.\"\"\"\n570\t+    if state.game_over:\n571\t+        return \"win\" if state.won else \"loss\"\n572\t+    revealed = sum(1 for ch in state.secret_word if ch in state.guessed_letters)\n573\t+    total = len(state.secret_word)\n574\t+    if revealed == total - 1 and total > 1:\n575\t+        return \"near_win\"\n576\t+    if revealed > 0:\n577\t+        return \"progress\"\n578\t+    return \"start\"\n579\t+\n580\t+\n581\t+def _glyph(stage: str, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n582\t+    \"\"\"Get the growth stage glyph.\"\"\"\n583\t+    glyphs = _GROWTH_ASCII if ascii_mode else _GROWTH_EMOJI\n584\t+    return glyphs[stage]\n585\t+\n586\t+\n587\t+def render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n588\t+    \"\"\"Render the full turn display.\"\"\"\n589\t+    stage = _growth_stage(state)\n590\t+    glyph = _glyph(stage, ascii_mode)\n591\t+    title = f\"{glyph} Word Garden\"\n592\t+\n593\t+    word_display = display_word(state)\n594\t+    guessed_display = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters)) if state.guessed_letters else \"\"\n595\t+\n596\t+    if ascii_mode:\n597\t+        water_str = f\"Water: {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water} [{_WATER_ASCII * state.remaining_water}]\"\n598\t+        weed_str = f\"Weeds: {state.weed_count} [{_WEED_ASCII * state.weed_count}]\"\n599\t+    else:\n600\t+        water_str = f\"Water: {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water} {_WATER_EMOJI * state.remaining_water}\"\n601\t+        weed_str = f\"Weeds: {state.weed_count} {_WEED_EMOJI * state.weed_count}\"\n602\t+\n603\t+    lines = [\n604\t+        title,\n605\t+        \"\",\n606\t+        f\"Word:     {word_display}\",\n607\t+    ]\n608\t+\n609\t+    if guessed_display:\n610\t+        lines.append(f\"Guessed:  {guessed_display}\")\n611\t+    else:\n612\t+        lines.append(\"Guessed:\")\n613\t+\n614\t+    lines.extend([\n615\t+        water_str,\n616\t+        weed_str,\n617\t+    ])\n618\t+\n619\t+    if state.status_message:\n620\t+        lines.extend([\"\", state.status_message])\n621\t+\n622\t+    lines.append(\"\")\n623\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n624\t+\n625\t+\n626\t+def win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n627\t+    \"\"\"Render the win screen.\"\"\"\n628\t+    glyph = _glyph(\"win\", ascii_mode)\n629\t+    lines = [\n630\t+        f\"{glyph} Bloom!\",\n631\t+        \"\",\n632\t+        f\"You guessed the word: {state.secret_word}\",\n633\t+        \"The garden is thriving.\",\n634\t+    ]\n635\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n636\t+\n637\t+\n638\t+def loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n639\t+    \"\"\"Render the loss screen.\"\"\"\n640\t+    glyph = _glyph(\"loss\", ascii_mode)\n641\t+    lines = [\n642\t+        f\"{glyph} The garden ran out of water.\",\n643\t+        \"\",\n644\t+        f\"The word was: {state.secret_word}\",\n645\t+        \"Try again and grow a new garden.\",\n646\t+    ]\n647\t+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n648\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"01bed81f-a45c-4496-9976-ee8a208a5a4e","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:52:53.983Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates/B.diff","content":"diff --git a/README.md b/README.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..49153b9\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/README.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,80 @@\n+# Word Garden\n+\n+A friendly terminal word-guessing game. Guess the hidden word before the garden runs out of water. It is like Hangman, but with plants instead of gallows.\n+\n+Word Garden is a small TUI game designed as a more cheerful alternative to Hangman. It is intended as a slightly more adventurous \"Hello World\" project for testing AI-assisted software development. The game includes input validation, state management, a simple loop, win/loss conditions, and a friendly terminal interface.\n+\n+## How to Play\n+\n+Start the game:\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m word_garden\n+```\n+\n+The game will display a masked word and prompt you for a letter guess. Each correct guess reveals matching letters and helps your garden grow. Each incorrect guess costs water and allows weeds to spread.\n+\n+Win by revealing all the letters before the garden runs out of water.\n+\n+## Options\n+\n+**Difficulty levels:**\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty easy      # 8 water, 4–6 letter words\n+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty normal    # 6 water, 5–8 letter words (default)\n+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty hard      # 4 water, 7+ letter words\n+```\n+\n+**ASCII mode (no emoji):**\n+\n+```bash\n+python3 -m word_garden --ascii\n+```\n+\n+## Rules\n+\n+- The game picks a random secret word.\n+- You guess one letter at a time.\n+- A correct guess reveals all matching positions and helps your plant grow.\n+- An incorrect guess costs one water and adds a weed.\n+- You win by revealing the entire word.\n+- You lose if the garden runs out of water before the word is complete.\n+\n+## Example Game\n+\n+```\n+🌱 Word Garden\n+\n+Word:     _ _ _ _ _ _\n+Guessed:\n+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧💧\n+Weeds:\n+\n+Guess a letter: a\n+\n+Good guess! The garden grows.\n+\n+Word:     _ A _ _ _ _\n+Guessed:  A\n+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧💧\n+Weeds:\n+\n+Guess a letter: z\n+\n+No match. A weed appears.\n+\n+Word:     _ A _ _ _ _\n+Guessed:  A Z\n+Water:   💧💧💧💧💧\n+Weeds:   🌿\n+```\n+\n+## Accessibility\n+\n+The game supports both emoji and ASCII modes. In ASCII mode, water and weeds are shown as counts with text labels, so the game is fully playable without emoji support.\n+\n+```\n+Water: 5/6 [*****]\n+Weeds: 1 [-]\n+```\ndiff --git a/tests/test_ui.py b/tests/test_ui.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..fff5e7b\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_ui.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,360 @@\n+import random\n+import unittest\n+from io import StringIO\n+\n+from word_garden.game import GameState, new_game\n+from word_garden.ui import render, win_screen, loss_screen\n+from word_garden.main import main\n+\n+\n+class TestRender(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test the render() function for both emoji and ASCII modes.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_render_emoji_at_start(self):\n+        \"\"\"Emoji render includes title, word, water, weeds, growth glyph.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters=set(),\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🌱 Word Garden\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"_ _ _ _ _ _\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 6/6 💧💧💧💧💧💧\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 0\", output)\n+\n+    def test_render_emoji_with_guesses(self):\n+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows guessed letters sorted.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"E\"},\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"Good guess!\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"_ A R _ E _\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:  A E R\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Good guess!\", output)\n+\n+    def test_render_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n+        \"\"\"ASCII render contains no emoji characters.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\"},\n+            remaining_water=4,\n+            weed_count=2,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 4/6 [****]\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 2 [--]\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"*\", output)  # ASCII plant\n+\n+    def test_render_emoji_progress_stage(self):\n+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows progress glyph when some letters guessed.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"D\"},\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🌿 Word Garden\", output)\n+\n+    def test_render_emoji_near_win_stage(self):\n+        \"\"\"Emoji render shows near-win glyph when almost all letters guessed.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"},\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🌷 Word Garden\", output)\n+\n+    def test_render_with_status_message(self):\n+        \"\"\"Render includes status message on its own line.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters=set(),\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"No match. A weed appears.\", output)\n+\n+    def test_render_ascii_water_count(self):\n+        \"\"\"ASCII mode shows water count with label.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters=set(),\n+            remaining_water=3,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=False,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Water: 3/6\", output)\n+\n+\n+class TestWinScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test the win_screen() function.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_win_screen_emoji(self):\n+        \"\"\"Win screen shows bloom emoji, word, and thriving message.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"You guessed the word: GARDEN. The garden is thriving.\",\n+            game_over=True,\n+            won=True,\n+        )\n+        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"You guessed the word: GARDEN\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output)\n+\n+    def test_win_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n+        \"\"\"Win screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n+            remaining_water=6,\n+            weed_count=0,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=True,\n+            won=True,\n+        )\n+        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output)\n+\n+\n+class TestLossScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test the loss_screen() function.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_loss_screen_emoji(self):\n+        \"\"\"Loss screen shows wilted emoji, word, and try-again message.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n+            remaining_water=0,\n+            weed_count=6,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"The garden ran out of water. The word was: GARDEN.\",\n+            game_over=True,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"The word was: GARDEN\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output)\n+\n+    def test_loss_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n+        \"\"\"Loss screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n+        state = GameState(\n+            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n+            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n+            remaining_water=0,\n+            weed_count=6,\n+            max_water=6,\n+            status_message=\"\",\n+            game_over=True,\n+            won=False,\n+        )\n+        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🥀\", output)\n+        self.assertIn(\"* The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test main() game loop completes successfully.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_end_to_end_with_all_alphabet(self):\n+        \"\"\"E2E: game runs and completes with all alphabet guesses.\"\"\"\n+        outputs = []\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text)\n+\n+        guesses = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n+        guess_index = [0]\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            if guess_index[0] >= len(guesses):\n+                raise EOFError()\n+            letter = guesses[guess_index[0]]\n+            guess_index[0] += 1\n+            return letter\n+\n+        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Word Garden\", output_str)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", output_str)\n+        self.assertTrue(output_str.count(\"Bloom!\") > 0 or output_str.count(\"The garden ran out of water\") > 0)\n+\n+    def test_end_to_end_ascii_mode(self):\n+        \"\"\"E2E: game in ASCII mode uses no emoji.\"\"\"\n+        outputs = []\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text)\n+\n+        guesses = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n+        guess_index = [0]\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            if guess_index[0] >= len(guesses):\n+                raise EOFError()\n+            letter = guesses[guess_index[0]]\n+            guess_index[0] += 1\n+            return letter\n+\n+        result = main([\"--ascii\", \"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🥀\", output_str)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output_str)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output_str)\n+        self.assertNotIn(\"🌷\", output_str)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainEndToEndLoss(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a loss.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_end_to_end_loss(self):\n+        \"\"\"E2E: scripted loss game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n+        outputs = []\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text)\n+\n+        def fake_input_gen():\n+            wrong_letters = \"ZYXWVUTSRQPON\"\n+            for letter in wrong_letters:\n+                yield letter\n+\n+        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            try:\n+                letter = next(inputs)\n+                return letter\n+            except StopIteration:\n+                raise EOFError()\n+\n+        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output_str)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output_str)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainInvalidInputRePrompt(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test that invalid input re-prompts without consuming a turn.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_invalid_then_valid(self):\n+        \"\"\"Invalid input should re-prompt; valid input should advance.\"\"\"\n+        rng = random.Random(42)\n+        state = new_game(\"normal\", rng=rng)\n+\n+        guesses = [\"\", \"A\"] + sorted(state.secret_word)[1:]\n+\n+        outputs = []\n+        guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            try:\n+                return next(guess_iter)\n+            except StopIteration:\n+                raise EOFError()\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text + end)\n+\n+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Please enter a single letter.\", output_str)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Good guess! The garden grows.\", output_str)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainEOFGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test that EOF (Ctrl-D) exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_eof_exit_code(self):\n+        \"\"\"EOF should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n+        outputs = []\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            raise EOFError()\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text + end)\n+\n+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\n+\n+\n+class TestMainKeyboardInterruptGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n+    \"\"\"Test that Ctrl-C exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exit_code(self):\n+        \"\"\"KeyboardInterrupt should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n+        outputs = []\n+\n+        def fake_input():\n+            raise KeyboardInterrupt()\n+\n+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n+            outputs.append(text + end)\n+\n+        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n+\n+        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n+        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n+        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\ndiff --git a/word_garden/__main__.py b/word_garden/__main__.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..70ba871\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/__main__.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+import sys\n+from .main import main\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    sys.exit(main())\ndiff --git a/word_garden/main.py b/word_garden/main.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..eeb1943\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/main.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,66 @@\n+import argparse\n+import sys\n+\n+from .game import new_game, validate_guess, apply_guess\n+from .ui import render, win_screen, loss_screen\n+\n+\n+def main(argv=None, input_fn=None, output_fn=None) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Run the Word Garden game loop.\n+\n+    Args:\n+        argv: Command-line arguments (default: sys.argv[1:])\n+        input_fn: Injectable input function (default: input)\n+        output_fn: Injectable output function (default: print)\n+\n+    Returns:\n+        Exit code (0 on success or EOF/interrupt)\n+    \"\"\"\n+    if input_fn is None:\n+        input_fn = input\n+    if output_fn is None:\n+        output_fn = print\n+\n+    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n+        prog=\"word_garden\",\n+        description=\"A friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n+    )\n+    parser.add_argument(\n+        \"--difficulty\",\n+        choices=[\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"],\n+        default=\"normal\",\n+        help=\"Game difficulty (default: normal)\",\n+    )\n+    parser.add_argument(\n+        \"--ascii\",\n+        action=\"store_true\",\n+        help=\"Use ASCII-only output (no emoji)\",\n+    )\n+\n+    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n+\n+    state = new_game(args.difficulty)\n+\n+    try:\n+        while not state.game_over:\n+            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n+            output_fn(\"Guess a letter: \", end=\"\")\n+            user_input = input_fn()\n+\n+            letter, error = validate_guess(user_input)\n+            if error:\n+                output_fn(error)\n+                continue\n+\n+            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n+\n+        if state.won:\n+            output_fn(win_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n+        else:\n+            output_fn(loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n+\n+        return 0\n+\n+    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n+        output_fn(\"\\nThanks for playing! Goodbye.\")\n+        return 0\ndiff --git a/word_garden/ui.py b/word_garden/ui.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..fb1c250\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/word_garden/ui.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,106 @@\n+from .game import GameState, display_word\n+\n+# Growth stage glyphs\n+_GROWTH_EMOJI = {\n+    \"start\": \"🌱\",\n+    \"progress\": \"🌿\",\n+    \"near_win\": \"🌷\",\n+    \"win\": \"🌻\",\n+    \"loss\": \"🥀\",\n+}\n+\n+_GROWTH_ASCII = {\n+    \"start\": \"*\",\n+    \"progress\": \"*\",\n+    \"near_win\": \"*\",\n+    \"win\": \"*\",\n+    \"loss\": \"*\",\n+}\n+\n+_WATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\n+_WATER_ASCII = \"*\"\n+\n+_WEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n+_WEED_ASCII = \"-\"\n+\n+\n+def _growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Determine the current growth stage.\"\"\"\n+    if state.game_over:\n+        return \"win\" if state.won else \"loss\"\n+    revealed = sum(1 for ch in state.secret_word if ch in state.guessed_letters)\n+    total = len(state.secret_word)\n+    if revealed == total - 1 and total > 1:\n+        return \"near_win\"\n+    if revealed > 0:\n+        return \"progress\"\n+    return \"start\"\n+\n+\n+def _glyph(stage: str, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Get the growth stage glyph.\"\"\"\n+    glyphs = _GROWTH_ASCII if ascii_mode else _GROWTH_EMOJI\n+    return glyphs[stage]\n+\n+\n+def render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Render the full turn display.\"\"\"\n+    stage = _growth_stage(state)\n+    glyph = _glyph(stage, ascii_mode)\n+    title = f\"{glyph} Word Garden\"\n+\n+    word_display = display_word(state)\n+    guessed_display = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters)) if state.guessed_letters else \"\"\n+\n+    if ascii_mode:\n+        water_str = f\"Water: {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water} [{_WATER_ASCII * state.remaining_water}]\"\n+        weed_str = f\"Weeds: {state.weed_count} [{_WEED_ASCII * state.weed_count}]\"\n+    else:\n+        water_str = f\"Water: {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water} {_WATER_EMOJI * state.remaining_water}\"\n+        weed_str = f\"Weeds: {state.weed_count} {_WEED_EMOJI * state.weed_count}\"\n+\n+    lines = [\n+        title,\n+        \"\",\n+        f\"Word:     {word_display}\",\n+    ]\n+\n+    if guessed_display:\n+        lines.append(f\"Guessed:  {guessed_display}\")\n+    else:\n+        lines.append(\"Guessed:\")\n+\n+    lines.extend([\n+        water_str,\n+        weed_str,\n+    ])\n+\n+    if state.status_message:\n+        lines.extend([\"\", state.status_message])\n+\n+    lines.append(\"\")\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n+\n+\n+def win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Render the win screen.\"\"\"\n+    glyph = _glyph(\"win\", ascii_mode)\n+    lines = [\n+        f\"{glyph} Bloom!\",\n+        \"\",\n+        f\"You guessed the word: {state.secret_word}\",\n+        \"The garden is thriving.\",\n+    ]\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n+\n+\n+def loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Render the loss screen.\"\"\"\n+    glyph = _glyph(\"loss\", ascii_mode)\n+    lines = [\n+        f\"{glyph} The garden ran out of water.\",\n+        \"\",\n+        f\"The word was: {state.secret_word}\",\n+        \"Try again and grow a new garden.\",\n+    ]\n+    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n","numLines":648,"startLine":1,"totalLines":648}}},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":50,"estimated_tokens_delta":50,"uuid":"12e02aad-3da1-4d60-a054-d79f9d83f10e","session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":100,"estimated_tokens_delta":50,"uuid":"b253ac61-03f1-4190-a883-c098f40d2e7e","session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":250,"estimated_tokens_delta":150,"uuid":"59293dc1-41c2-4c60-bb30-c93917b3386a","session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":350,"estimated_tokens_delta":100,"uuid":"a454d025-fea6-44dd-9bd5-43b62d1bb16b","session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2"}