 collapses every ASCII stage to a constant `*`** — no progress feedback in the exact mode the fallback exists for.\n- **Test rigor:** A pins the secret word and positively asserts the specific win/loss screens. **B's only e2e \"win\" test asserts a tautological `Bloom! OR ran-out-of-water` disjunction on the global RNG** (passed 40/40 *because* it can't fail), and another test reads a `Random(42)` word then drives `main([])` on the global RNG — both forbidden by the standing tips.\n- **I/O contract:** A calls `output_fn(text)` with one positional arg and passes the prompt to `input_fn`. **B raises `TypeError` on a minimal `output_fn(text)`** because it relies on `print`'s `end=` kwarg.\n\nA is correct and complete as-is, so ADOPT rather than SYNTHESIZE.\n\n### `.code-tips.md` additions ([2026-06-12, task-002])\n- New **UI/rendering** section: ASCII fallback must preserve every information channel (no constant-glyph collapse); status rows need label+count not symbols alone; multi-line end screens are distinct from one-line `status_message`; near-win must use distinct-letter sets.\n- Sharpened the **I/O-split** entry: `output_fn` must work as a single-positional sink.\n- Reconfirmed the **vacuous-OR e2e** and **scenario-pinning** rules with this round's concrete failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":439,"cache_read_input_tokens":104416,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":439},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","uuid":"ebddbcf3-0df4-4187-9019-354904a1c3a8","request_id":"req_011CbxhVXJnU5MYF1DfBCmXN"},{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":585399,"duration_api_ms":583268,"ttft_ms":9235,"ttft_stream_ms":2165,"time_to_request_ms":33,"num_turns":47,"result":"Review complete. Everything is in the working tree; no `git add`/`commit` performed. Engine files untouched.\n\n## Verdict: **ADOPT Candidate A**\n\n### Protocol executed in order\n1. **Blind sketch** written first (`blind-sketch.md`) before opening any diff.\n2. **Context** read: SPEC.md, `.code-tips.md`, adopted engine (`game.py`/`words.py`).\n3. **Candidates** read anonymously (A, B; **C is an empty 0-byte diff — non-submission**).\n4. **Empirical verification** in detached scratch worktrees at base `61b16c8`, both worktrees removed afterward. Sealed worker worktrees never inspected.\n5. **`review.md`** + **`verdict.json`** written.\n6. **`.code-tips.md`** distilled.\n\n### Why A\nBoth A and B pass every mechanical gate (A: 75 tests, B: 66; compileall clean; piped-EOF exit 0; engine byte-identical). A wins on the discriminators verified by behavioural probe:\n\n- **ASCII parity:** A's growth stage varies in ASCII (`*`/`**`/`***`); **B collapses every ASCII stage to a constant `*`** — no progress feedback in the exact mode the fallback exists for.\n- **Test rigor:** A pins the secret word and positively asserts the specific win/loss screens. **B's only e2e \"win\" test asserts a tautological `Bloom! OR ran-out-of-water` disjunction on the global RNG** (passed 40/40 *because* it can't fail), and another test reads a `Random(42)` word then drives `main([])` on the global RNG — both forbidden by the standing tips.\n- **I/O contract:** A calls `output_fn(text)` with one positional arg and passes the prompt to `input_fn`. **B raises `TypeError` on a minimal `output_fn(text)`** because it relies on `print`'s `end=` kwarg.\n\nA is correct and complete as-is, so ADOPT rather than SYNTHESIZE.\n\n### `.code-tips.md` additions ([2026-06-12, task-002])\n- New **UI/rendering** section: ASCII fallback must preserve every information channel (no constant-glyph collapse); status rows need label+count not symbols alone; multi-line end screens are distinct from one-line `status_message`; near-win must use distinct-letter sets.\n- Sharpened the **I/O-split** entry: `output_fn` must work as a single-positional sink.\n- Reconfirmed the **vacuous-OR e2e** and **scenario-pinning** rules with this round's concrete failures.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"49b5c3ab-f3ba-421a-aede-9dac6abc1ea2","total_cost_usd":3.399600500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":5568,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89522,"cache_read_input_tokens":2796195,"output_tokens":43030,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89522,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1019,"cache_read_input_tokens":104416,"cache_creation_input_tokens":439,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":439},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":2623,"outputTokens":14,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.002693,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":5568,"outputTokens":43030,"cacheReadInputTokens":2796195,"cacheCreationInputTokens":89522,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.3969075,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_0191aMGLqMWPnznsCF5kEpcT","tool_input":{"command":"cd /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4\nBASE=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\necho \"base=$BASE\"\nCAND=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates\nfor X in A B; do\n  echo \"===== Setting up review-$X =====\"\n  git worktree add ../review-$X --detach HEAD >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo \"worktree added\"\n  git -C ../review-$X apply $CAND/$X.diff && echo \"applied $X\" || echo \"APPLY FAILED $X\"\ndone\ngit worktree list","description":"Create worktrees A and B, apply diffs"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PNuUFj61JKadLJ9H5Mx94G","tool_input":{"command":"REPO=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4\nCAND=$REPO/.farnsworth/task-002/candidates\nfor X in A B; do\n  echo \"===== review-$X =====\"\n  git -C \"$REPO\" worktree add \"$REPO/../review-$X\" --detach HEAD >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo \"worktree added\"\n  git -C \"$REPO/../review-$X\" apply \"$CAND/$X.diff\" && echo \"applied $X OK\" || echo \"APPLY FAILED $X\"\ndone\ngit -C \"$REPO\" worktree list","description":"Create worktrees A and B, apply diffs"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01H6PSETDTwNBJR1MtjUQvAY","tool_input":{"command":"for X in A B; do\n  echo \"################## CANDIDATE $X ##################\"\n  W=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-$X\n  echo \"--- unittest ---\"\n  (cd \"$W\" && python3 -m unittest discover -s tests 2>&1 | tail -8)\n  echo \"--- compileall ---\"\n  (cd \"$W\" && python3 -m compileall -q word_garden 2>&1 && echo \"compileall OK rc=$?\")\n  echo \"--- piped EOF run ---\"\n  (cd \"$W\" && printf '' | python3 -m word_garden >/dev/null 2>&1; echo \"exit=$?\")\n  echo \"--- engine untouched vs base ---\"\n  git -C /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4 diff --quiet HEAD -- word_garden/game.py word_garden/words.py && echo \"(repo engine clean)\"\n  diff -q \"$W/word_garden/game.py\" /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/game.py && echo \"game.py identical\"\n  diff -q \"$W/word_garden/words.py\" /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/words.py && echo \"words.py identical\"\ndone","description":"Run gate: unittest, compileall, piped run, engine integrity"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_017A8fvvj4kUVr5dGPL1hYio","tool_input":{"command":"cd /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A\necho \"=== A: unittest ===\"; python3 -m unittest discover -s tests 2>&1 | tail -6\necho \"=== A: compileall ===\"; python3 -m compileall -q word_garden 2>&1; echo \"rc=$?\"\necho \"=== A: piped EOF run ===\"; printf '' | python3 -m word_garden >/dev/null 2>&1; echo \"exit=$?\"\necho \"=== A: engine identical? ===\"\ndiff -q word_garden/game.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/game.py && echo game-OK\ndiff -q word_garden/words.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/words.py && echo words-OK","description":"Gate for candidate A"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_018Y3jedn26M3AEYY8NGhNL1","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -m compileall -q /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A/word_garden 2>&1; echo \"compileall rc=$?\"","description":"A compileall"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VNfnTeeZZCsPpEJVt98tP9","tool_input":{"command":"printf '' | PYTHONPATH=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A python3 -m word_garden >/dev/null 2>&1; echo \"piped-EOF exit=$?\"\ndiff -q /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A/word_garden/game.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/game.py && echo \"game.py identical\"\ndiff -q /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A/word_garden/words.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/words.py && echo \"words.py identical\"","description":"A piped run + engine integrity"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_016Gophjer5XW2JncnN3thDR","tool_input":{"command":"printf '' | PYTHONPATH=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A python3 -m word_garden >/dev/null 2>&1\necho \"piped-EOF exit=$?\"","description":"A piped EOF run exit code"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01L4F3rHPJQPt1LoSP96r9nr","tool_input":{"command":"diff -q /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A/word_garden/game.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/game.py && diff -q /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A/word_garden/words.py /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/word_garden/words.py && echo \"A engine identical\"","description":"A engine integrity"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QMEMPLkK3beybwp1AxCwLP","tool_input":{"command":"printf '' | env PYTHONPATH=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A python3 -m word_garden > /tmp/wg_A_piped.out 2>&1\necho \"piped-EOF exit=$?\"","description":"A piped run exit code"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y9beW1SLpwNf5UCUKayKo1","tool_input":{"file_path":"/tmp/probe.py","content":"import sys, io\n\n# worktree path is injected via PYTHONPATH; candidate label via argv[1]\nLABEL = sys.argv[1]\nfrom word_garden import main as M\nfrom word_garden import ui as U\nfrom word_garden import game as G\n\nresults = []\ndef check(name, cond, extra=\"\"):\n    results.append((name, bool(cond), extra))\n\nclass Rec:\n    def __init__(self, inputs):\n        self.it = iter(inputs); self.out = []\n    def inp(self, prompt=\"\"):\n        try: return next(self.it)\n        except StopIteration: raise EOFError\n    # accept end= to be compatible with candidates that pass it\n    def outp(self, text=\"\", end=\"\\n\"):\n        self.out.append(str(text))\n    @property\n    def text(self): return \"\\n\".join(self.out)\n\ndef run_main(argv, inputs):\n    r = Rec(inputs)\n    try:\n        code = M.main(argv, input_fn=r.inp, output_fn=r.outp)\n    except SystemExit as e:\n        return None, e.code, r\n    return code, None, r\n\n# ---- 1. scripted WIN via injected I/O (pin word) ----\nimport word_garden.words as W\norig = W.select_word\nW.select_word = lambda diff=\"normal\", rng=None: \"GARDEN\"\ntry:\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    check(\"scripted win returns 0\", code == 0, f\"code={code} sysx={sysx}\")\n    check(\"scripted win shows bloom/word\", (\"GARDEN\" in r.text and (\"Bloom\" in r.text or \"thriving\" in r.text)), r.text[-120:])\n    # ---- 2. scripted LOSS (6 wrong, normal water=6) ----\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n    check(\"scripted loss returns 0\", code == 0, f\"code={code}\")\n    check(\"loss reveals word GARDEN\", \"GARDEN\" in r.text and (\"ran out of water\" in r.text or \"water\" in r.text.lower()), r.text[-160:])\n    # ---- 3. invalid input consumes no water ----\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([], [\"\", \"7\", \"!\", \"$$\"] + list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    # full game still won despite leading invalids => no water lost to them\n    check(\"invalid input -> still wins (no water consumed)\", \"GARDEN\" in r.text and (\"Bloom\" in r.text or \"thriving\" in r.text), r.text[-120:])\n    # ---- 4. --ascii whole game incl end screens is pure ASCII ----\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--ascii\",\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    check(\"ascii full WIN game pure ASCII\", r.text.isascii(), repr([c for c in r.text if not c.isascii()][:10]))\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--ascii\",\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n    check(\"ascii full LOSS game pure ASCII\", r.text.isascii(), repr([c for c in r.text if not c.isascii()][:10]))\n    # ---- 5. --difficulty changes water (first frame) ----\n    code, sysx, re_ = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"easy\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    code, sysx, rn_ = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"hard\"], list(\"ZQXJB\"))\n    check(\"easy water 8 in first frame\", \"8/8\" in re_.out[0] or \"8\" in re_.out[0], re_.out[0][:80])\n    check(\"hard water 4 in first frame\", \"4/4\" in rn_.out[0] or \"4\" in rn_.out[0], rn_.out[0][:80])\nfinally:\n    W.select_word = orig\n\n# ---- 6. --help exits 0, bad difficulty exits 2 ----\ncode, sysx, r = run_main([\"--help\"], [])\ncheck(\"--help exits 0\", sysx == 0, f\"sysx={sysx}\")\ncode, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"bogus\"], [])\ncheck(\"bad difficulty exits 2\", sysx == 2, f\"sysx={sysx}\")\n\n# ---- 7. growth stages change with progress (emoji render) ----\ndef mk(**kw):\n    d = dict(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set(), remaining_water=6, weed_count=0, max_water=6)\n    d.update(kw); return G.GameState(**d)\nstart = U.render(mk())\nprog  = U.render(mk(guessed_letters={\"G\",\"A\"}))\nnear  = U.render(mk(guessed_letters={\"G\",\"A\",\"R\",\"D\",\"E\"}))\ncheck(\"growth: start != progress render\", start != prog, \"\")\ncheck(\"growth: progress != near-win render\", prog != near, \"\")\n# ---- 8. ui.py has no print/input ----\nimport inspect\nsrc = inspect.getsource(U)\ncheck(\"ui.py no print(\", \"print(\" not in src, \"\")\ncheck(\"ui.py no input(\", \"input(\" not in src.replace(\"input_fn\",\"\").replace(\"_input\",\"\"), \"\")\n\nprint(f\"==== PROBE RESULTS for {LABEL} ====\")\nallpass = True\nfor name, ok, extra in results:\n    allpass &= ok\n    print(f\"[{'PASS' if ok else 'FAIL'}] {name}\" + (f\"   <<{extra}>>\" if (not ok and extra) else \"\"))\nprint(\"ALL PASS\" if allpass else \"SOME FAILED\")\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Li46CLY4F3HikP7oEbNyJ3","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/probe.py","content":"import sys\n\nLABEL = sys.argv[1]\nfrom word_garden import main as M\nfrom word_garden import ui as U\nfrom word_garden import game as G\n\nresults = []\ndef check(name, cond, extra=\"\"):\n    results.append((name, bool(cond), extra))\n\nclass Rec:\n    def __init__(self, inputs):\n        self.it = iter(inputs); self.out = []\n    def inp(self, prompt=\"\"):\n        try: return next(self.it)\n        except StopIteration: raise EOFError\n    def outp(self, text=\"\", end=\"\\n\"):\n        self.out.append(str(text))\n    @property\n    def text(self): return \"\\n\".join(self.out)\n\ndef run_main(argv, inputs):\n    r = Rec(inputs)\n    try:\n        code = M.main(argv, input_fn=r.inp, output_fn=r.outp)\n    except SystemExit as e:\n        return None, e.code, r\n    return code, None, r\n\nimport word_garden.words as W\norig = W.select_word\nW.select_word = lambda diff=\"normal\", rng=None: \"GARDEN\"\ntry:\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    check(\"scripted win returns 0\", code == 0, f\"code={code} sysx={sysx}\")\n    check(\"scripted win shows bloom/word\", (\"GARDEN\" in r.text and (\"Bloom\" in r.text or \"thriving\" in r.text)), r.text[-160:])\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n    check(\"scripted loss returns 0\", code == 0, f\"code={code}\")\n    check(\"loss reveals word GARDEN\", \"GARDEN\" in r.text and \"water\" in r.text.lower(), r.text[-200:])\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([], [\"\", \"7\", \"!\", \"$$\"] + list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    check(\"invalid input -> still wins (no water consumed)\", (\"GARDEN\" in r.text and (\"Bloom\" in r.text or \"thriving\" in r.text)), r.text[-160:])\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--ascii\",\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    check(\"ascii full WIN game pure ASCII\", r.text.isascii(), repr([c for c in r.text if not c.isascii()][:12]))\n    code, sysx, r = run_main([\"--ascii\",\"--difficulty\",\"normal\"], list(\"ZQXJKW\"))\n    check(\"ascii full LOSS game pure ASCII\", r.text.isascii(), repr([c for c in r.text if not c.isascii()][:12]))\n    code, sysx, re_ = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"easy\"], list(\"GARDEN\"))\n    code, sysx, rn_ = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"hard\"], list(\"ZQXJB\"))\n    check(\"easy water 8 in first frame\", \"8\" in re_.out[0], re_.out[0][:90])\n    check(\"hard water 4 in first frame\", \"4\" in rn_.out[0], rn_.out[0][:90])\nfinally:\n    W.select_word = orig\n\ncode, sysx, r = run_main([\"--help\"], [])\ncheck(\"--help exits 0\", sysx == 0, f\"sysx={sysx}\")\ncode, sysx, r = run_main([\"--difficulty\",\"bogus\"], [])\ncheck(\"bad difficulty exits 2\", sysx == 2, f\"sysx={sysx}\")\n\ndef mk(**kw):\n    d = dict(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set(), remaining_water=6, weed_count=0, max_water=6)\n    d.update(kw); return G.GameState(**d)\nstart = U.render(mk())\nprog  = U.render(mk(guessed_letters={\"G\",\"A\"}))\nnear  = U.render(mk(guessed_letters={\"G\",\"A\",\"R\",\"D\",\"E\"}))\ncheck(\"growth: start != progress render\", start != prog, \"\")\ncheck(\"growth: progress != near-win render\", prog != near, \"\")\n\nimport inspect\nsrc = inspect.getsource(U)\ncheck(\"ui.py no print(\", \"print(\" not in src, \"\")\n\nprint(f\"==== PROBE RESULTS for {LABEL} ====\")\nallpass = True\nfor name, ok, extra in results:\n    allpass &= ok\n    print(f\"[{'PASS' if ok else 'FAIL'}] {name}\" + (f\"   <<{extra}>>\" if (not ok and extra) else \"\"))\nprint(\"ALL PASS\" if allpass else \"SOME FAILED\")\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01TkXusYdNMdKUJc7jk7e4fW","tool_input":{"command":"env PYTHONPATH=/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/review-A python3 /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/word-garden-4/.farnsworth/task-002/_probe.py A 2>&1","description":"Run behavioural probes for candidate A"}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"70735b4a-29d7-4ee5-8d42-727ae8a4ba82"}]
